name: Walmart
description: Walmart Inc. is an American multinational retail corporation that operates a chain of hypermarkets, discount department stores, and grocery stores. The company was founded by Sam Walton in 1962 and incorporated on October 31, 1969. Walmart is one of the largest retail corporations in the world and is known for its wide range of products, including electronics, clothing, groceries, and household items. It also operates online e-commerce platforms, offering a variety of goods for sale. With a presence in multiple countries, Walmart is a prominent player in the global retail industry.

name: Amazon
description: Amazon.com, Inc. is an American multinational technology company that focuses on e-commerce, digital streaming, cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and more. It is one of the Big Five companies in the U.S. information technology industry, alongside Google, Apple, Microsoft, and Facebook. Amazon is known for its e-commerce platform, Amazon.com, as well as its Amazon Prime subscription service, Amazon Web Services (AWS), and a variety of other ventures. The company was founded by Jeff Bezos in 1994 and has grown to become one of the largest and most influential technology companies in the world.

name: Exxon Mobil
description: Exxon Mobil Corporation is an American multinational corporation known for its involvement in the oil and gas industry. It is a publicly traded company that was formed in 1999 through the merger of Exxon and Mobil. Exxon Mobil is one of the largest publicly traded companies in the world and is involved in all aspects of the oil and gas industry, including exploration, production, refining, and distribution. The company is also active in the petrochemical industry and has operations in numerous countries around the world. Exxon Mobil is known for its technological innovations and has a long history of involvement in the energy sector.

name: Apple
description: Apple Inc. is an American multinational technology company that designs, develops, and sells consumer electronics, computer software, and online services. The company's hardware products include the iPhone smartphone, iPad tablet computer, Mac personal computer, Apple Watch smartwatch, and Apple TV digital media player. Apple's software includes the macOS and iOS operating systems, the iTunes media player, the Safari web browser, and the iLife and iWork creativity and productivity suites. Apple was founded in 1976 by Steve Jobs, Steve Wozniak, and Ronald Wayne.

name: UnitedHealth Group
industry: Health Care: Insurance and Managed Care
description: UnitedHealth Group Incorporated is an American for-profit managed health care company that offers a wide range of health insurance products and services. It is the largest healthcare company in the world by revenue, providing health care coverage for individuals and employers. The company's services include health insurance, pharmaceutical benefit management, healthcare technology, and data analytics. UnitedHealth Group operates through two main platforms: UnitedHealthcare for health benefits and Optum for health services. The company is known for its innovation in the healthcare industry and its efforts to improve healthcare outcomes and affordability.

name: CVS Health
industry: Health Care: Pharmacy and Other Services
description: CVS Health Corporation is an American healthcare company that owns pharmacies, health clinics, and a pharmacy benefit manager. The company was founded in 1963, originally as Consumer Value Stores, and has since grown to become one of the largest pharmacy chains in the United States. CVS Health operates over 9,900 retail locations across the country and provides a wide range of healthcare services, including prescription fulfillment, over-the-counter medications, health clinics, and pharmacy benefits management services for insurance companies and employers. In addition to its retail pharmacies, CVS Health also owns the health insurer Aetna, which it acquired in 2018 to further expand its presence in the healthcare industry.

name: Berkshire Hathaway
description: Berkshire Hathaway Inc. is an American multinational conglomerate holding company headquartered in the United States. The company was founded by renowned investor Warren Buffett and his business partner Charlie Munger. Berkshire Hathaway owns a diverse range of businesses in various sectors, including insurance, utilities, energy, manufacturing, and retail. The company is known for its long-term investment strategy and has a significant ownership stake in several well-known companies.

name: Alphabet
description: Alphabet Inc. is an American multinational conglomerate company created through a corporate restructuring of Google on October 2, 2015. It is the parent company of Google and several other businesses previously owned by or tied to Google. These businesses include Waymo (self-driving cars), Verily (life sciences), and X Development (moonshot projects), among others. Alphabet Inc. is known for its diverse range of products and services, with Google being the most well-known and widely used.

name: McKesson
description: McKesson Corporation is an American company providing pharmaceutical distribution services, medical supplies, and healthcare information technology. It is one of the largest healthcare companies in the world, serving as an intermediary between manufacturers and healthcare providers. McKesson also offers services such as pharmacy automation, clinical support, and business analytics to improve the efficiency and delivery of healthcare services.

name: Chevron
description: Chevron Corporation is an American multinational energy corporation engaged in every aspect of the oil, natural gas, and geothermal energy industries, including exploration and production; refining, marketing, and transport; chemicals manufacturing and sales; and power generation. Chevron is one of the world's largest oil companies and has operations in more than 180 countries. The company traces its roots back to the founding of the Pacific Coast Oil Co. in 1879. Chevron has a strong presence in the United States as well as in international markets.

name: AmerisourceBergen
description: AmerisourceBergen Corporation is an American pharmaceutical sourcing and distribution company. It is one of the largest pharmaceutical distributors in the United States, serving both healthcare providers and pharmaceutical manufacturers. The company's services include drug distribution, inventory management, consulting services, and various other solutions for the healthcare industry. AmerisourceBergen operates in multiple countries and is a key player in the healthcare supply chain.

name: Costco Wholesale
description: Costco Wholesale Corporation, commonly known as Costco, is an American multinational corporation that operates a chain of membership-only warehouse clubs. As of 2021, Costco was the fifth largest retailer in the world and the world's largest retailer of choice and prime beef, organic foods, rotisserie chicken, and wine. Costco was founded in 1983 in Seattle, Washington, by James Sinegal and Jeffrey Brotman. The company's business model relies on high sales volumes and quick inventory turnover, with members paying an annual fee for access to discounted prices on a wide range of products. Costco operates over 800 warehouse clubs worldwide, selling a variety of products including groceries, appliances, electronics, clothing, and more.

name: Microsoft
description: Microsoft Corporation is an American multinational technology company that develops, manufactures, licenses, supports, and sells computer software, consumer electronics, personal computers, and related services. Founded by Bill Gates and Paul Allen on April 4, 1975, Microsoft is best known for its Windows operating systems and Office suite of productivity software. Microsoft has expanded its product line to include cloud computing services (Azure), video game consoles (Xbox), and hardware devices such as Surface tablets and laptops. Microsoft is one of the world's largest technology companies and is considered a major player in the tech industry.

name: Cardinal Health
description: Cardinal Health, Inc. is a multinational health care services company that specializes in the distribution of pharmaceuticals and medical products, providing innovative solutions to both healthcare providers and manufacturers to improve the efficiency and quality of healthcare. In addition to distribution services, Cardinal Health offers services such as medical product manufacturing, medication management and compliance, and consulting services to healthcare facilities. The company is committed to helping customers streamline their operations and enhance patient care.

name: Cigna
industry: Health Care: Pharmacy and Other Services
description: Cigna Corporation is an American multinational managed healthcare and insurance company. It is headquartered in the United States and offers a wide range of health insurance products and related services, including medical, dental, disability, life and accident insurance. Cigna also provides healthcare management services aimed at improving the health, well-being, and productivity of its customers. With a focus on quality and affordability, Cigna serves individuals, employers, healthcare professionals, and other groups around the world.

name: Marathon Petroleum
description: Marathon Petroleum Corporation is an American petroleum refining, marketing, and transportation company. It was formed on July 1, 2011, as a result of a split from Marathon Oil. The company operates refineries in several locations across the United States and is involved in the refining, marketing, and transportation of petroleum products. Marathon Petroleum Corporation is one of the largest petroleum refining companies in the United States, with a strong presence in the industry.

name: Phillips 66
description: Phillips 66 is an American multinational energy company that was created as a result of the split of ConocoPhillips in 2012. It operates in the midstream, chemicals, refining, and marketing sectors. The company is involved in the processing, transportation, and marketing of oil and natural gas. Phillips 66 is headquartered in the United States and has a significant presence in the energy industry globally.

name: Valero Energy
description: Valero Energy Corporation is an American multinational energy company that is headquartered in San Antonio, Texas. It is one of the largest independent petroleum refiners in the United States and operates 15 refineries with a combined capacity of approximately 3.1 million barrels per day. Valero is also involved in the production and marketing of fuels and other petrochemical products. Additionally, the company is engaged in renewable energy initiatives, such as the production of ethanol and biodiesel. Valero Energy Corporation is known for its focus on refining and marketing, as well as its extensive retail network of branded gas stations across the United States, Canada, and the Caribbean.

name: Ford Motor
description: Ford Motor Company is an American multinational automaker headquartered in Dearborn, Michigan. It was founded by Henry Ford on June 16, 1903. The company sells automobiles and commercial vehicles under the Ford brand and most luxury cars under the Lincoln brand. Ford also owns Brazilian SUV manufacturer Troller, an 8% stake in Aston Martin of the United Kingdom and a 32% stake in Jiangling Motors. It also has joint-ventures in China (Changan Ford), Taiwan (Ford Lio Ho), Thailand (AutoAlliance Thailand), Turkey (Ford Otosan), and Russia (Ford Sollers). Ford is the second-largest U.S.-based automaker (preceded by General Motors) and the fifth-largest in the world.

name: Home Depot
description: The Home Depot, Inc. is an American home improvement retail company that sells tools, construction products, and services. It operates many big-box format stores across the United States, as well as in Canada and Mexico. The company's stores offer a wide range of products for DIY home improvement projects, including appliances, tools, hardware, lumber, building materials, paint, plumbing, flooring, garden supplies, and more. Home Depot also provides installation services for various products sold in their stores.

name: General Motors
description: General Motors Company (GM) is an American multinational corporation that designs, manufactures, markets, and distributes vehicles and vehicle parts. It was founded in 1908 and has since grown to become one of the largest automakers in the world. GM produces a wide range of vehicles, including cars, trucks, and SUVs, under various brands such as Chevrolet, GMC, Buick, and Cadillac. The company also has a strong presence in electric vehicles through its Chevrolet Bolt EV and upcoming GMC Hummer EV models. GM has operations in over 30 countries and sells vehicles in more than 100 countries worldwide.

name: Elevance Health
industry: Health Care: Insurance and Managed Care
description: Elevance Health, Inc. is a health technology company focused on improving mental health and well-being. The company utilizes advanced data science and machine learning to create personalized digital solutions for individuals seeking mental health support. Elevance Health aims to provide accessible and effective tools to help individuals manage and improve their mental well-being.

name: JPMorgan Chase
description: JPMorgan Chase & Co. is an American multinational investment bank and financial services holding company. It is considered one of the largest banks in the United States and a major player in the financial sector globally. JPMorgan Chase is a leading provider of various financial services, including investment banking, commercial banking, asset management, and private banking. The company has a significant presence in the United States and operates in over 100 countries worldwide. JPMorgan Chase was formed in 2000 through the merger of Chase Manhattan Corporation and J.P. Morgan & Co.

name: Kroger
description: Kroger is an American retail company founded in 1883 by Bernard Kroger. It is the largest supermarket chain by revenue and the second-largest general retailer in the United States. With over 2,800 stores across 31 states, Kroger operates under various banners, including Kroger, Fred Meyer, Ralphs, Harris Teeter, and more. In addition to traditional grocery items, Kroger also offers pharmacy services, fuel centers, and online shopping options. The company is known for its commitment to customer satisfaction, community involvement, and innovation in the retail industry.

name: Centene
industry: Health Care: Insurance and Managed Care
description: Centene Corporation is a healthcare company that provides a portfolio of services to government-sponsored healthcare programs, focusing on under-insured and uninsured individuals. The company offers a range of healthcare solutions including health plans, specialty services, and managed care solutions through its various subsidiaries. Centene Corporation operates in multiple states in the United States and serves millions of members across its different healthcare programs. The company is known for its commitment to improving the healthcare outcomes of its members while controlling costs.

name: Verizon Communications
description: Verizon Communications Inc. is an American multinational telecommunications conglomerate and a corporate component of the Dow Jones Industrial Average. The company operates a vast network that provides a wide range of communication services, including wireless and wireline voice and data services, video and data services, and network solutions for businesses. Verizon is one of the largest telecommunications companies in the United States and serves millions of customers nationwide.

name: Walgreens Boots Alliance
description: Walgreens Boots Alliance, Inc. is an American holding company that owns Walgreens, a chain of pharmacy stores, health and wellness services, and provides a variety of health and beauty products. The company was formed in December 2014 through the merger of Walgreen Company and Alliance Boots, a multinational pharmacy-led health and beauty group based in the United Kingdom. Walgreens Boots Alliance operates retail stores in various formats across the United States and internationally, offering pharmaceuticals, wellness products, and health-related services.

name: Federal National Mortgage Association
description: The Federal National Mortgage Association (FNMA), commonly known as Fannie Mae, is a government-sponsored enterprise (GSE) that was established in 1938 to provide liquidity, stability, and affordability to the U.S. housing and mortgage markets. Fannie Mae does this by purchasing and guaranteeing mortgages, thereby allowing lenders to provide more affordable home loans to a wider range of borrowers. Fannie Mae plays a crucial role in the U.S. housing market by facilitating the flow of mortgage funds, promoting access to homeownership, and stabilizing the housing market during economic fluctuations.

name: Comcast
description: Comcast Corporation is an American telecommunications conglomerate that operates through three primary segments: Comcast Cable, NBCUniversal, and Sky. Comcast Cable is one of the largest providers of cable television, internet, and telephone services in the United States. NBCUniversal is a media and entertainment company that owns and operates a portfolio of television networks, film studios, and theme parks. Sky is a British media and telecommunications company that offers satellite television and broadband services. Comcast Corporation is known for its significant presence in the media and entertainment industry, as well as its expansive telecommunications infrastructure.

name: AT&T
description: AT&T Inc. is an American multinational conglomerate holding company that is the parent company of AT&T Communications, which is the largest provider of mobile and fixed telephone services in the United States. The company also offers broadband subscription television services through DirecTV. Additionally, AT&T operates the WarnerMedia subsidiary, which includes HBO, Turner Broadcasting System, and Warner Bros. The company is known for its telecommunications, media, and entertainment services, and it has a significant presence in the telecommunications industry worldwide.

name: Meta Platforms
description: Meta Platforms, Inc. (formerly known as Facebook, Inc.) is an American multinational technology conglomerate based in Menlo Park, California. Founded by Mark Zuckerberg, along with his college roommates Andrew McCollum, Eduardo Saverin, Chris Hughes, and Dustin Moskovitz, the company was originally launched as TheFacebook on February 4, 2004. Meta Platforms is known for its social networking platform Facebook, as well as for acquiring other popular social media platforms such as Instagram, WhatsApp, and Oculus VR. The company's mission is to "give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together."

name: Bank of America
description: Bank of America Corporation is an American multinational investment bank and financial services company headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina. It is one of the largest banks in the United States, offering a wide range of financial products and services, including consumer banking, wealth management, and investment banking. The company operates through various segments, including Consumer Banking, Global Wealth and Investment Management, Global Banking, Global Markets, and All Other. With a history dating back to 1904, Bank of America has grown to become a major player in the banking industry, serving millions of customers worldwide.

name: Target
description: Target Corporation is an American retail corporation founded in 1902. It is the eighth-largest retailer in the United States, operating over 1,900 stores in North America. Target offers a wide range of products, including clothing, accessories, electronics, home goods, and groceries. The company is known for its trendy merchandise and collaborations with designers and brands. Target also operates an online store, offering customers the convenience of shopping from home.

name: Dell Technologies
description: Dell Technologies Inc. is an American multinational technology company that develops, sells, repairs, and supports computers and related products and services. The company was founded by Michael Dell in 1984 and has grown to become one of the largest technology corporations in the world. Dell Technologies offers a wide range of products including personal computers, servers, data storage devices, network switches, software, and computer peripherals. The company is known for its direct sales model, which allows customers to customize their products and purchase directly from Dell.

name: Archer Daniels Midland
description: Archer Daniels Midland Company (ADM) is an American global food processing and commodities trading corporation. It was founded in 1902 and is one of the largest agricultural processors and food ingredient providers in the world. ADM operates through several business segments, including agriculture services, oilseeds processing, corn processing, and more. The company processes crops such as corn, oilseeds, wheat, and cocoa to create ingredients for food, animal feed, industrial, and energy uses. ADM also trades in commodities such as grains, oilseeds, wheat, and cocoa.

name: Citigroup
description: Citigroup Inc. is an American multinational investment bank and financial services corporation. It was formed from one of the world's largest mergers in history when Citicorp merged with Travelers Group in 1998. Today, Citigroup operates in more than 160 countries and jurisdictions, offering a wide range of financial products and services including consumer banking, corporate and investment banking, securities brokerage, wealth management, and private banking.

name: UPS
description: UPS, or United Parcel Service, is an American multinational package delivery and supply chain management company. It is one of the largest shipping and logistics companies in the world, providing a broad range of services including transportation, distribution, freight forwarding, and contract logistics. UPS is known for its distinctive brown delivery trucks and uniforms, as well as its extensive global network that reaches over 220 countries and territories. The company was founded in 1907 and has since grown to become a leader in the industry, delivering millions of packages every day to businesses and consumers worldwide.

name: Pfizer
description: Pfizer Inc. is an American multinational pharmaceutical corporation that was founded in 1849. It is one of the world's largest pharmaceutical companies and operates globally, with a focus on developing and producing a wide range of medicines and vaccines. Pfizer is involved in research and development, manufacturing, and marketing of prescription medications across various therapeutic areas including immunology, oncology, cardiology, and neuroscience. The company has a long history of significant contributions to healthcare and is known for producing widely used medications such as Viagra, Lipitor, and Prevnar.

name: Lowe's
description: Lowe's Companies, Inc. is a home improvement retailer operating in the United States and Canada. The company was founded in 1921 and has since grown to become one of the largest home improvement retailers in North America. Lowe's offers a wide range of products for home improvement, renovation, maintenance, and repair, including appliances, tools, furniture, and building materials. The company operates both physical stores and an online platform, providing customers with convenient access to a wide selection of products for their home improvement needs.

name: Johnson & Johnson
description: Johnson & Johnson is an American multinational corporation that develops medical devices, pharmaceuticals, and consumer packaged goods. Founded in 1886, it is one of the largest healthcare companies in the world. The company's products range from medical devices used in surgeries and diagnostics to over-the-counter pharmaceuticals and personal care products. Johnson & Johnson has a presence in over 60 countries and has a strong focus on innovation and sustainability in the healthcare industry.

name: FedEx
description: FedEx Corporation is an American multinational conglomerate that focuses on providing a diverse range of transportation, e-commerce, and business services. The company was founded in 1971 and has grown to become a global leader in logistics, offering express shipping, freight services, and supply chain management solutions. FedEx is known for its distinctive overnight shipping service and innovative tracking technology, which revolutionized the industry. The company operates through various subsidiaries, including FedEx Express, FedEx Ground, FedEx Freight, FedEx Logistics, and FedEx Services, serving millions of customers worldwide. With a strong commitment to sustainability and corporate social responsibility, FedEx continues to expand its operations and capabilities to meet the evolving needs of the global marketplace.

name: Humana
industry: Health Care: Insurance and Managed Care
description: Humana Inc. is a for-profit American health insurance company based in Louisville, Kentucky. It offers a range of health insurance products and services, including medical, dental, vision, and pharmaceutical plans. Humana also provides wellness programs, Medicare plans, and Medicaid services. The company serves over 20 million customers across the United States and has a strong focus on promoting health and wellness through various initiatives and programs.

name: Energy Transfer
description: Energy Transfer LP is a company engaged in the natural gas and propane transportation and storage business. It is one of the largest and most diversified energy companies in the United States, with a portfolio of approximately 90,000 miles of pipelines and associated infrastructure. The company's operations also include natural gas midstream and intrastate transportation and storage, as well as natural gas liquids transportation and services. Energy Transfer LP serves various customers, including utility companies, electric power generators, and industrial companies.

name: Freddie Mac
description: Freddie Mac, or the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation, is a public government-sponsored enterprise (GSE) in the United States. It was established in 1970 to provide stability, liquidity, and affordability to the country's residential mortgage market. Freddie Mac purchases and guarantees mortgages originated by lenders, thereby allowing them to provide more funding to homebuyers. The company plays a vital role in the housing market by promoting homeownership and affordable housing.

name: PepsiCo
description: PepsiCo, Inc. is an American multinational corporation that operates in the food, snack, and beverage industries. The company was formed in 1965 through the merger of Pepsi-Cola and Frito-Lay and has since grown to become one of the largest food and beverage companies in the world. PepsiCo's product portfolio includes a wide range of popular brands such as Pepsi, Lay's, Gatorade, Tropicana, Quaker Oats, and Doritos. The company is known for its focus on innovation, sustainability, and corporate social responsibility.

name: Wells Fargo
description: Wells Fargo & Company is an American multinational financial services company that provides a wide range of banking, investment, mortgage, and consumer finance services. It is one of the largest banks in the United States, with operations worldwide. The company was founded in 1852 and has grown to become a major player in the financial services industry. Wells Fargo is known for its retail banking services, as well as its wealth management and investment banking businesses.

name: Walt Disney
description: The Walt Disney Company, commonly known as Disney, is an American diversified multinational entertainment and media conglomerate headquartered in Burbank, California. It was originally founded on October 16, 1923, by Walt Disney and Roy O. Disney as the Disney Brothers Cartoon Studio; it also operated under the names The Walt Disney Studio and Walt Disney Productions before officially changing its name to The Walt Disney Company in 1986. The company is known for its film studio division, the Walt Disney Studios, which includes Walt Disney Pictures, Walt Disney Animation Studios, Pixar, Marvel Studios, Lucasfilm, 20th Century Fox, and Searchlight Pictures. Disney's other main divisions are Disney Media Networks, Disney Parks, Experiences and Products, and Disney Direct-to-Consumer & International.

name: ConocoPhillips
description: ConocoPhillips is an American multinational energy corporation engaged in hydrocarbon exploration. It is one of the world's largest independent exploration and production (E&P) companies. With operations in several countries, ConocoPhillips focuses on producing oil, natural gas, natural gas liquids, and bitumen. Additionally, the company is involved in refining, marketing, and transporting petroleum products. ConocoPhillips was formed through the merger of Conoco Inc. and Phillips Petroleum Company in 2002, and has since grown to become a significant player in the energy industry.

name: Tesla
description: Tesla, Inc. is an American electric vehicle and clean energy company founded in 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning. The company is named after the famous inventor and electrical engineer Nikola Tesla. Tesla designs, manufactures, and sells electric cars, battery energy storage systems, and solar panels. It is known for its innovative electric vehicles, including the Tesla Roadster, Model S, Model 3, Model X, and Model Y. Tesla is also a major player in the development of autonomous driving technology and renewable energy solutions.

name: Procter & Gamble
description: Procter & Gamble (P&G) is a multinational consumer goods company that specializes in a wide range of personal care and household products. P&G was founded in 1837 by William Procter and James Gamble in the United States. The company has since grown to become one of the largest and most successful consumer goods companies in the world. P&G's product portfolio includes well-known brands such as Pampers, Tide, Gillette, Pantene, and Crest, among many others. The company is known for its focus on innovation, quality, and sustainability in its products.

name: General Electric
description:
General Electric Company (GE) is an American multinational conglomerate corporation incorporated in New York. As of 2021, the company operates through a number of segments, including aviation, healthcare, power, renewable energy, digital industry, additive manufacturing, venture capital, and finance.
 
GE is one of the largest and most diversified industrial corporations in the world, with products ranging from aircraft engines, power generation, and water processing to medical imaging, business and consumer financing, media content, and industrial products. The company has a long history, tracing its roots back to inventor Thomas Edison, and has been a pioneer in numerous industries throughout its existence.

name: Albertsons
description: Albertsons Companies, Inc. is an American grocery company founded and headquartered in the United States. It is one of the largest food and drug retailers in the country, with a strong presence in various states. The company operates a wide range of grocery store formats, including supermarkets, combination food and drug stores, and warehouse stores. Albertsons Companies also owns several well-known retail brands, each offering a variety of products and services to customers. The company is focused on providing quality and convenient shopping experiences for consumers across its diverse portfolio of stores.

name: MetLife
description: MetLife, Inc. is a leading global provider of insurance, annuities, and employee benefit programs. It was founded in 1868 and has since grown to become one of the largest insurance companies in the world. MetLife operates in over 60 countries and serves more than 90 million customers worldwide. The company offers a wide range of insurance products, including life insurance, disability income insurance, and dental insurance, as well as retirement and savings solutions. MetLife is known for its strong commitment to innovation, customer service, and financial stability.

name: Goldman Sachs Group
description: The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. is an American multinational investment bank and financial services company. It offers a range of financial services, including investment banking, asset management, securities, and other financial services primarily to institutional clients. Goldman Sachs is known for its involvement in global financial markets and its role as a primary dealer in the U.S. Treasury securities market. The company was founded in 1869 and has grown to become one of the leading financial institutions in the world.

name: Sysco
description: Sysco Corporation is an American multinational corporation involved in marketing and distributing food products, smallwares, kitchen equipment, and tabletop items to restaurants, healthcare and educational facilities, hospitality businesses, and other institutional customers. With over 57,000 employees, Sysco is one of the largest foodservice distributors in the United States. The company operates approximately 330 distribution facilities worldwide and serves over 600,000 customer locations. Sysco was founded in 1969 and has grown to become a prominent player in the foodservice industry.

name: Raytheon Technologies
description: Raytheon Technologies Corporation is an American multinational aerospace and defense technology company formed in 2020 through the merger of Raytheon Company and United Technologies Corporation. The company operates in four key segments: Collins Aerospace, Pratt & Whitney, Raytheon Intelligence & Space, and Raytheon Missiles & Defense. Raytheon Technologies is a leading producer of advanced technologies in areas such as aircraft engines, avionics, cybersecurity, missiles, and air defense systems. The company is a major supplier to the U.S. Department of Defense and international defense forces.

name: Boeing
description: Boeing is an American multinational corporation that designs, manufactures, and sells airplanes, rotorcraft, rockets, satellites, telecommunications equipment, and missiles worldwide. The company also provides leasing and product support services. Boeing is among the largest global aerospace manufacturers and is the second-largest defense contractor in the world based on revenue.

name: StoneX Group
description: StoneX Group Inc., formerly known as INTL FCStone Inc., is a financial services firm that provides institutional clients with a wide range of financial services including trade execution, clearing, and advisory services across asset classes. The company's services include commodity trading, foreign exchange, securities, and wealth management. StoneX Group Inc. serves clients in more than 130 countries and has a global presence in major financial centers. The company was founded in 1924 and has since grown to become a leading provider of financial services to institutional clients worldwide.

name: Lockheed Martin
description: Lockheed Martin Corporation is an American aerospace, defense, arms, security, and advanced technologies company with worldwide interests. It was formed by the merger of Lockheed Corporation with Martin Marietta in March 1995. The company is engaged in the research, design, development, manufacture, integration, and sustainment of advanced technology systems, products, and services. Lockheed Martin operates in four primary business segments: Aeronautics, Missiles and Fire Control, Rotary and Mission Systems, and Space. The company is known for its involvement in designing and producing military aircraft, such as the F-16 Fighting Falcon, F-22 Raptor, F-35 Lightning II, and more. Additionally, Lockheed Martin plays a crucial role in various space exploration projects and national defense initiatives.

name: Morgan Stanley
description: Morgan Stanley is an American multinational investment bank and financial services company. It offers a range of financial services including investment banking, securities trading, wealth management, and asset management. The company serves corporations, governments, institutions, and individuals around the world. Morgan Stanley is known for its prominent role in mergers and acquisitions, and is considered one of the leading investment banks globally.

name: Intel
description: Intel Corporation is an American multinational corporation and technology company that is known for designing and manufacturing semiconductor chips and other technology products. Founded in 1968, Intel is one of the world's largest and highest-valued semiconductor chip makers, based on revenue. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including computer systems, smartphones, tablets, data centers, and various other electronic devices. Intel is also a leading player in the development of technologies such as artificial intelligence, autonomous driving, and 5G connectivity.

name: HP
description: HP Inc. is an American multinational information technology company that develops personal computers, printers, and related supplies. It was formed in 2015 as part of the splitting of the original Hewlett-Packard company, with HP Inc. handling the personal systems and printing business, while Hewlett Packard Enterprise focused on enterprise products and services. HP Inc. has a long history in the technology industry and is known for its innovation in computing and printing solutions. The company serves consumers, small and medium-sized businesses, and large enterprises worldwide.

name: TD Synnex
description: TD SYNNEX Corporation is an American multinational information technology company. It provides services in technology distribution, logistics, and integration. The company offers a wide range of services including IT distribution, cloud services, data center solutions, and technology services. TD SYNNEX Corporation serves a diverse range of customers including resellers, system integrators, retailers, and original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) around the world. The company was formed as a result of the merger of Tech Data and SYNNEX Corporation in 2021.

name: IBM
description: International Business Machines Corporation (IBM) is an American multinational technology company that produces and sells computer hardware, software, and services. IBM was founded in 1911 and has a long history of innovation in the technology industry. The company's products and services range from mainframe computers to cloud computing solutions, artificial intelligence, and blockchain technology. IBM is known for its research and development efforts, as well as its corporate culture focused on diversity and inclusion.

name: HCA Healthcare
description: HCA Healthcare, Inc. is an American for-profit operator of healthcare facilities. It is one of the largest healthcare systems in the United States and operates a network of hospitals, surgery centers, urgent care centers, and physician practices. HCA Healthcare was founded in 1968 and has since grown to have facilities in several states across the country. The company is known for providing a wide range of healthcare services, including general acute care, emergency care, outpatient surgery, rehabilitation, and behavioral health services.

name: Prudential Financial
description: Prudential Financial, Inc. is an American Fortune 500 company and one of the largest insurance and financial services providers in the United States. The company offers a wide range of products and services, including life insurance, annuities, retirement-related services, mutual funds, and investment management. Prudential Financial, Inc. has a long history, dating back to its founding in 1875, and has grown to become a prominent player in the insurance and financial services industry. It is known for its strong commitment to customer service and financial stability.

name: Caterpillar
description: Caterpillar Inc. is an American Fortune 100 corporation that designs, manufactures, markets, and sells machinery, engines, financial products, and insurance to customers via a worldwide dealer network. The company is a leading manufacturer of construction and mining equipment, diesel and natural gas engines, industrial gas turbines, and diesel-electric locomotives. Caterpillar also provides financial services through its subsidiary, Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation. With more than 90 years of experience in the industry, Caterpillar is recognized for its quality products and innovative solutions for various industries worldwide.

name: Merck
description: Merck & Co., Inc., also known as Merck Sharp & Dohme (MSD) outside the United States and Canada, is an American multinational pharmaceutical company. Founded in 1891, Merck is one of the largest pharmaceutical companies in the world, developing prescription medicines, vaccines, biologic therapies, and animal health products. The company is known for its contributions to medical research and development, with a focus on addressing unmet medical needs and improving healthcare worldwide.

name: World Fuel Services
description: World Fuel Services is a global energy management company involved in providing energy procurement, supply chain management, and logistics services to various industries and organizations worldwide. The company primarily focuses on the aviation, marine, and land transportation sectors, offering fuel and related services to help clients efficiently manage their energy needs. With operations in over 200 countries, World Fuel Services aims to provide tailored energy solutions to meet the diverse requirements of its customers across the globe.

name: Enterprise Products Partners
description: Enterprise Products Partners L.P. is an American natural gas and crude oil pipeline company with headquarters in Houston, Texas. It is one of the largest publicly traded partnerships and a leading North American provider of midstream energy services. The company operates a diversified network of natural gas, natural gas liquids, crude oil, and refined products pipelines, as well as storage facilities. Enterprise Products Partners L.P. serves a wide range of customers, including producers, consumers, and investors in the energy industry.

name: AbbVie
description: AbbVie Inc. is an American publicly traded biopharmaceutical company founded in 2013 as a spin-off of Abbott Laboratories. The company focuses on the development and commercialization of pharmaceuticals, including immunology, oncology, neuroscience, and virology products. AbbVie is known for its flagship drug, Humira, which is a leading treatment for autoimmune diseases. The company is headquartered in the United States and operates globally, with a commitment to advancing research and innovation in the healthcare industry.

name: Plains GP Holdings
description: Plains GP Holdings, L.P. is a publicly traded master limited partnership in the United States. It is involved in the transportation, storage, terminalling, and marketing of crude oil and refined products. Plains GP Holdings, L.P. serves as the general partner of Plains All American Pipeline, L.P., another MLP engaged in the transportation and storage of crude oil and natural gas liquids. The company was founded in 2013 and has since become a major player in the energy industry.

name: Dow
description: Dow Inc. is an American multinational chemical corporation that was spun off from DowDuPont in April 2019. It is one of the largest chemical producers in the world and provides a wide range of products and solutions in various sectors, including packaging, infrastructure, transportation, consumer care, and electronics. Dow Inc. is known for its innovation and sustainability efforts in developing products that address global challenges while also focusing on corporate responsibility and environmental stewardship.

name: AIG
description: American International Group, Inc. (AIG) is an American multinational finance and insurance corporation with operations in more than 80 countries and jurisdictions. AIG provides a range of property casualty insurance, life insurance, retirement products, and other financial services. The company was founded in 1919 and has grown to become one of the largest insurance organizations in the world.

name: American Express
description: American Express Company, also known as Amex, is an American multinational financial services corporation. The company is known for its credit card, charge card, and traveler's cheque businesses. American Express operates in several segments, including Global Consumer Services Group, Global Commercial Services, Global Merchant and Network Services, and Corporate & Other. The company was founded in 1850 and is one of the 30 components of the Dow Jones Industrial Average.

name: Charter Communications
description: Charter Communications, Inc. is an American telecommunications and mass media company that offers a range of services to consumers and businesses. It is the fifth-largest telephone provider based on residential subscriber line count. It serves more than 31 million customers in 41 states. Charter Communications provides cable television, high-speed internet, and telephone services. The company was founded in 1993 and has since grown to become a major player in the telecommunications industry in the United States.

name: Tyson Foods
description: Tyson Foods, Inc. is an American multinational corporation operating in the food industry. It is one of the largest producers of meat products, including chicken, beef, and pork. The company also offers a wide range of prepared foods and other meat-based products. Tyson Foods is headquartered in the United States and has a significant presence in the global food market. With a history dating back to the 1930s, Tyson Foods has grown to become a major player in the food industry, known for its diverse product offerings and distribution network.

name: Deere
description: Deere & Company is an American corporation that manufactures agricultural, construction, and forestry machinery, diesel engines, drivetrains (axles, transmissions, gearboxes) used in heavy equipment, and lawn care equipment. The company was founded in 1837 by John Deere, a blacksmith and inventor, and has since grown to become one of the leading providers of agricultural equipment worldwide. With a wide range of products catering to various industries, Deere & Company is known for its iconic green and yellow machinery, including tractors, combines, sprayers, and excavators.

name: Cisco Systems
description: Cisco Systems, Inc. is an American multinational technology conglomerate that designs, manufactures, and sells networking equipment. It was founded in December 1984 by Leonard Bosack and Sandy Lerner. Cisco is known for its networking hardware, software, and telecommunications equipment, which are used to power the internet and networks worldwide. The company specializes in networking technologies related to routing and switching, as well as security, collaboration, cloud, and IoT solutions. Cisco also offers services such as technical support, advanced services, and cybersecurity services.

name: Allstate
description: Allstate Corporation is an American insurance company that offers a wide range of insurance products, including auto, home, renters, life, and business insurance. It was founded in 1931 and is one of the largest insurance providers in the United States. The company is known for its "You're in good hands with Allstate" slogan and the iconic Allstate Good Hands logo. Allstate also provides various financial products and services, such as retirement and investment planning.

name: Delta Air Lines
description: Delta Air Lines, Inc. is a major American airline, headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia. It operates over 5,000 flights daily and serves an extensive domestic and international network that includes over 300 destinations in more than 50 countries. Delta is known for its fleet size, route network, and passenger traffic, making it one of the largest and most successful airlines in the world. The company was founded in 1924 and has grown to become a prominent player in the aviation industry.

name: TJX
description: TJX Companies, Inc. is an American multinational off-price department store corporation, headquartered in the United States. It operates several chains of off-price retail stores, including T.J.Maxx, Marshalls, HomeGoods, Sierra, and Homesense. Founded in 1956, TJX is known for offering brand name and designer goods at discounted prices. The company has a presence in multiple countries and has grown to become one of the largest off-price retailer in the world.

name: Progressive
description: Progressive Corporation is an American insurance company. It is one of the largest providers of car insurance in the United States. The company also offers other types of insurance such as homeowners insurance, renters insurance, and life insurance. Progressive is known for its innovative approach to insurance, including the use of technology to streamline the claims process and provide customers with competitive rates. The company was founded in 1937 and has since grown to become a major player in the insurance industry.

name: American Airlines Group
description: American Airlines Group Inc. is a major American airline holding company based in the United States. It was formed on December 9, 2013, following the merger of AMR Corporation, the parent company of American Airlines, and US Airways Group. American Airlines Group operates an extensive international and domestic network with almost 6,800 flights per day to nearly 350 destinations in more than 50 countries. With its fleet of over 850 aircraft, American Airlines is one of the largest airlines in the world. The company is known for its frequent flyer program, AAdvantage, and for being a founding member of the Oneworld airline alliance.

name: Performance Food Group
description: Performance Food Group Company is an American company that markets and distributes food and related products. The company was founded in 1885 and has since grown to become one of the leading food distributors in the United States. Performance Food Group serves a wide range of customers, including restaurants, healthcare facilities, schools, and convenience stores. The company offers a diverse selection of products, including fresh produce, dairy, meat, seafood, and kitchen supplies. Performance Food Group is known for its reliable service and commitment to quality, making it a trusted partner for businesses in the foodservice industry.

name: PBF Energy
description: PBF Energy Inc. is a petroleum refiner and supplier of unbranded transportation fuels, heating oil, petrochemical feedstocks, lubricants, and other petroleum products. The company operates oil refineries in multiple locations in the United States, with a combined processing capacity of over 1 million barrels per day. PBF Energy Inc. was founded in 2008 and has since grown to become one of the largest independent petroleum refiners in North America.

name: Nike
description: NIKE, Inc. is an American multinational corporation that is engaged in the design, development, manufacturing, and worldwide marketing and sales of footwear, apparel, equipment, accessories, and services. The company is one of the world's largest suppliers of athletic shoes and apparel and a major manufacturer of sports equipment, with sales in more than 180 countries. Nike was founded in 1964 as Blue Ribbon Sports by Bill Bowerman and Phil Knight and officially became Nike, Inc. in 1971. The company is known for its iconic "swoosh" logo and its "Just Do It" slogan, which has become a globally recognized marketing tagline.

name: Best Buy
description: Best Buy Co., Inc. is a multinational consumer electronics retailer headquartered in the United States. The company was founded in 1966 and has since grown to become one of the largest consumer electronics retailers in the world. Best Buy operates both online and brick-and-mortar stores, offering a wide range of products including electronics, appliances, entertainment products, and services. With a focus on providing customers with the latest technology and a superior shopping experience, Best Buy has established itself as a leader in the consumer electronics industry.

name: Bristol-Myers Squibb
description: Bristol-Myers Squibb Company is an American pharmaceutical company that focuses on discovering, developing, and delivering innovative medicines for patients with serious diseases. The company's areas of focus include oncology, immunology, cardiovascular disease, and fibrosis. Bristol-Myers Squibb is known for developing and marketing a number of leading prescription drugs and has a global presence in the healthcare industry.

name: United Airlines Holdings
description: United Airlines Holdings, Inc. is an American publicly traded airline holding company headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. It was formed on December 30, 2019, as a result of the merger of United Continental Holdings, Inc. and the former United Airlines, Inc. United Airlines Holdings owns and operates United Airlines, one of the world's largest airlines with an extensive network of domestic and international routes. The company operates a large fleet of aircraft and offers passenger and cargo services to various destinations around the world.

name: Thermo Fisher Scientific
description: Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc. is an American multinational corporation that provides scientific research services, laboratory equipment, reagents, consumables, software, and services. The company was formed through the merger of Thermo Electron and Fisher Scientific in 2006. Thermo Fisher Scientific serves various industries, including healthcare, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, environmental monitoring, and academia. The company is a leading provider of analytical instruments, reagents, consumables, software, and services for research, manufacturing, analysis, discovery, and diagnostics.

name: Qualcomm
description: QUALCOMM Incorporated is an American multinational corporation that specializes in telecommunications equipment, semiconductors, and wireless technology. Founded in 1985, QUALCOMM is known for its development of technology used in mobile devices and other wireless communications systems. The company is a major player in the design and manufacturing of semiconductors for mobile phones, broadband networks, and other devices. QUALCOMM is also a prominent developer of 5G technology, providing solutions for the deployment of next-generation wireless networks.

name: Abbott Laboratories
description: Abbott Laboratories is an American multinational healthcare company with a range of branded generic pharmaceuticals, medical devices, diagnostics, and nutrition products. The company's areas of focus include cardiovascular products, diagnostic assays, diabetes care, and neuromodulation devices, among others. Abbott Laboratories has a global presence and is committed to advancing healthcare by developing innovative products and technologies to help people live healthier lives.

name: Coca-Cola
description: Coca-Cola is a carbonated soft drink manufactured by The Coca-Cola Company. It was originally invented in the late 19th century by a pharmacist named John Stith Pemberton. The drink's name refers to two of its original ingredients: coca leaves and kola nuts. Coca-Cola is one of the most popular and widely recognized beverages in the world, available in numerous countries and enjoyed by millions of people daily. The brand has expanded to include a variety of flavors and products, including Diet Coke, Coca-Cola Zero Sugar, and various other beverages.

name: Oracle
description: Oracle Corporation is an American multinational computer technology corporation headquartered in [location withheld]. The company provides database software and technology, cloud-engineered systems, and enterprise software products. Oracle's offerings include applications for customer relationship management, enterprise resource planning, and supply chain management, as well as servers, storage, and cloud solutions. Oracle is known for its flagship product, the Oracle Database, and has a strong presence in the enterprise software market.

name: Nucor
description: Nucor Corporation is a Fortune 250 company and one of the largest steel producers in North America. With a focus on sustainable practices and innovative technologies, Nucor is known for its commitment to environmental responsibility and product quality. The company operates multiple steel mills, recycling facilities, and downstream operations, serving various industries such as automotive, construction, and infrastructure. Nucor is recognized for its decentralized management structure and employee-centric culture, which have been instrumental in its success and growth over the years.

name: General Dynamics
description: General Dynamics Corporation is an American aerospace and defense company. It is one of the largest defense contractors in the world and is primarily engaged in the design, development, and manufacturing of defense products such as armored vehicles, munitions, combat systems, and IT solutions. General Dynamics serves both government and commercial customers and is known for its innovation and technological expertise in the defense industry.

name: Capital One Financial
description: Capital One Financial Corporation is an American bank holding company specializing in credit cards, auto loans, banking, and savings accounts. Founded in 1988, Capital One has become one of the largest banks in the United States based on deposits and assets. The company is known for its innovative use of technology and data analytics in financial services, as well as its aggressive marketing techniques. Capital One operates primarily in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom, providing a wide range of financial products and services to consumers, small businesses, and commercial clients.

name: HF Sinclair
description: HF Sinclair Corporation, commonly known as Sinclair Oil Corporation, is an American petroleum corporation that is privately owned. It is one of the largest privately-owned oil companies in the United States. Founded in 1916 by Harry F. Sinclair, the company is involved in all aspects of oil and gas exploration, production, refining, and distribution. Sinclair Oil is known for its iconic green dinosaur logo and operates a network of gas stations across the country. In addition to its petroleum business, Sinclair Oil also has interests in petrochemicals, transportation, and other related industries. The company is headquartered in the United States and has a long history in the American oil industry.

name: Dollar General
description: Dollar General Corporation is an American chain of variety stores that operates over 16,000 stores in the United States. The company is headquartered in Goodlettsville, Tennessee. With a focus on low-cost household goods, Dollar General offers a wide range of products, including food, snacks, health and beauty aids, cleaning supplies, household items, apparel, and seasonal items, at discounted prices. The company primarily targets customers in rural and suburban areas with convenient locations and affordable prices.

name: Arrow Electronics
description: Arrow Electronics, Inc. is a Fortune 500 company that specializes in the distribution and sales of electronic components and computer products. The company was founded in 1935 and has since grown to become one of the largest electronics distributors in the world. Arrow Electronics operates in over 90 countries and offers a wide range of products and services, including semiconductor and passive components, electromechanical products, and enterprise computing solutions. The company serves a diverse customer base that includes manufacturers, industrial companies, and technology firms, providing them with innovative solutions and supply chain services to help bring their products to market.

name: Occidental Petroleum
description: Occidental Petroleum Corporation is an American company engaged in hydrocarbon exploration in the United States, the Middle East, and Latin America. It is one of the largest oil producers in Texas and has operations in California as well. The company is involved in various aspects of the oil and gas industry, including exploration, production, and marketing. Occidental Petroleum was founded in 1920 and has since grown to become a major player in the global energy sector.

name: Travelers
description: Travelers Cos., Inc., commonly known as Travelers, is an American insurance company. It is the second-largest writer of U.S. commercial property casualty insurance, and the sixth-largest writer of U.S. personal insurance through independent agents. The company has operations in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, and Ireland. Travelers was founded in 1853 and has a long history in the insurance industry.

name: Northrop Grumman
description: Northrop Grumman Corporation is an American global aerospace and defense technology company. It is one of the world's largest defense contractors and ranks among the top defense companies globally. Northrop Grumman provides innovative systems, products, and solutions in autonomous systems, cyber, space, strike, and logistics and modernization to customers around the world. The company has a long history of involvement in various defense and technology projects, making it a key player in the aerospace and defense industry.

name: Honeywell International
description: Honeywell International Inc. is an American publicly traded conglomerate company that produces a variety of consumer and commercial products, engineering services, and aerospace systems. It operates through four main business segments: Aerospace, Home and Building Technologies, Performance Materials and Technologies, and Safety and Productivity Solutions. Honeywell is known for its innovative technology solutions in areas such as energy efficiency, safety, security, and productivity. The company has a global presence and serves customers in various industries, including aerospace, defense, energy, manufacturing, and healthcare.

name: 3M
description: 3M Company is an American multinational conglomerate corporation operating in the fields of industry, worker safety, US health care, and consumer goods. The company produces a variety of products, including adhesives, abrasives, laminates, passive fire protection, personal protective equipment, dental and orthodontic products, electronic materials, medical products, car-care products, electronic circuits, healthcare software, and optical films. 3M is known for its innovation, with notable inventions including the Post-it Note and the Scotch Tape. The company has a strong global presence and is considered a pioneer in research and development.

name: US Foods Holding
description: US Foods Holding Corp. is an American foodservice distributor headquartered in Rosemont, Illinois. The company supplies food and related products to over 250,000 customers, including restaurants, healthcare facilities, government entities, and educational institutions. US Foods Holding Corp. offers a wide range of products including fresh produce, meats, seafood, dairy, dry goods, and kitchen supplies. The company operates more than 60 distribution centers across the United States, making it one of the largest foodservice distributors in the country.

name: Warner Bros. Discovery
description: Warner Bros. Discovery, Inc. is a multinational mass media and entertainment conglomerate formed from the merger of WarnerMedia, a subsidiary of AT&T, and Discovery, Inc. The company operates a diverse range of businesses in television, film, and digital media. It is one of the largest and most well-known entertainment companies in the world, with a vast library of iconic films and TV shows. Warner Bros. Discovery, Inc. continues to produce and distribute content through various platforms to audiences globally.

name: Lennar
description: Lennar Corporation is a home construction and real estate company based in the United States. Founded in 1954, Lennar is one of the largest homebuilders in the country. The company operates in multiple states across the U.S. and offers a range of services including home construction, financial services, and asset management. Lennar is known for its focus on innovative home designs, quality construction, and customer satisfaction.

name: D.R. Horton
description: D.R. Horton, Inc. is an American residential construction company that was founded in 1978. It is one of the largest homebuilding companies in the United States. The company primarily focuses on the construction and sale of single-family homes, operating in multiple states across the country. D.R. Horton is known for its diverse range of home designs and flexible floor plans, catering to a wide variety of customers. In addition to homebuilding, the company also offers mortgage financing services to homebuyers.

name: Jabil
description: Jabil Inc. is an American worldwide manufacturing services company. Headquartered in the United States, Jabil provides comprehensive electronics design, production, and product management services to global electronics and technology companies. The company operates in over 25 countries and provides end-to-end product solutions for various industries, including healthcare, automotive, consumer electronics, and more. Jabil is known for its expertise in supply chain optimization, product design, and manufacturing innovation.

name: Cheniere Energy
description: Cheniere Energy is a Houston-based energy company engaged in liquefied natural gas (LNG) -related businesses. The company owns and operates the first liquefaction export facility in the United States, located in Louisiana. Cheniere Energy is a major player in the LNG industry, focusing on the production, transportation, and marketing of LNG. The company also has interests in natural gas pipelines and infrastructure. Founded in 1996, Cheniere Energy has become a significant player in the global energy market, particularly in the LNG sector.

name: Broadcom
description: Broadcom Inc. is a global technology company that designs, develops, and supplies a broad range of semiconductor and infrastructure software solutions. The company's product portfolio includes semiconductor devices, networking and storage equipment, and software for data center, networking, broadband, wireless, and industrial markets. Broadcom serves customers in various industries, including telecommunications, data center, enterprise networking, and the internet of things (IoT). The company was founded in 1961 and has since grown to become a leading player in the technology sector.

name: CarMax
description: CarMax, Inc. is a Fortune 500 company that operates as a retailer of used vehicles in the United States. It was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Richmond, Virginia. CarMax is known for its no-haggle pricing model and a wide selection of cars and financing options. The company has over 200 locations nationwide and has been recognized for its customer service and employee satisfaction.

name: Starbucks
description: Starbucks Corporation is an American multinational chain of coffeehouses and roastery reserves headquartered in Seattle, Washington. It is known for its high-quality coffee and espresso beverages, as well as a variety of pastries, snacks, and other food items. Starbucks is one of the largest coffeehouse chains in the world, operating thousands of locations globally. Founded in 1971, Starbucks has become a prominent and recognizable brand for coffee lovers worldwide.

name: Molina Healthcare
industry: Health Care: Insurance and Managed Care
description: Molina Healthcare, Inc. is a managed care company that provides health insurance to individuals and families who receive their care through Medicaid, Medicare, and through the health insurance marketplaces. The company was founded in 1980 by C. David Molina, MD, and is focused on serving low-income individuals and families. Molina Healthcare operates health plans in multiple states in the United States, offering a range of health insurance products and services to its members.

name: Uber Technologies
description: Uber Technologies, Inc., commonly known as Uber, is an American technology company. It operates a platform that connects users with transportation options, such as ride-sharing and food delivery services. Uber was founded in 2009 and has since expanded globally, becoming a prominent player in the sharing economy industry. With its innovative technology and user-friendly app, Uber has revolutionized the way people commute and order food in various cities around the world.

name: Philip Morris International
description: Philip Morris International Inc. is an American multinational cigarette and tobacco manufacturing company, with products sold in over 180 countries outside the United States. It is one of the largest tobacco companies in the world and is known for brands such as Marlboro, Parliament, and L&M. The company was established in 2008 when it was spun off from its former parent company, Altria Group. Philip Morris International focuses on the production and sale of cigarettes, smoke-free products, and other tobacco-related products globally.

name: Netflix
description: Netflix, Inc. is an American subscription-based streaming service that offers a wide variety of TV shows, movies, anime, documentaries, and more on thousands of internet-connected devices. Founded in 1997 by Reed Hastings and Marc Randolph in Scotts Valley, California, the company initially focused on DVD rental by mail before transitioning to a subscription-based streaming service in 2007. Netflix has since grown to become one of the largest streaming services globally, with millions of subscribers enjoying on-demand entertainment content. The company is known for its original content production, including popular series like "Stranger Things," "The Crown," and "House of Cards."

name: NRG Energy
description: NRG Energy, Inc. is an American energy company that produces electricity and provides energy solutions and services to customers in the United States. The company was founded in 1992 and is one of the largest independent power producers in the nation. NRG Energy operates a diverse portfolio of power generation facilities, including natural gas, coal, oil, nuclear, and renewable energy sources such as wind and solar. The company also offers retail electricity and natural gas services to residential, commercial, and industrial customers.

name: Mondelez International
description: Mondelez International, Inc. is an American multinational confectionery, food, holding, and beverage company based in the United States. It was established in 2012 after splitting from the Kraft Foods Inc. company. Mondelez International operates in more than 150 countries and is known for its wide range of products, including snacks, chocolate, gum, and candy. Some of the well-known brands owned by Mondelez International include Oreo, Cadbury, Toblerone, Trident, and Ritz. The company is one of the largest snack companies in the world, with a strong presence in both developed and emerging markets.

name: Danaher
description: Danaher Corporation is an American company with a diverse portfolio of businesses in the fields of life sciences, diagnostics, and environmental and applied solutions. The company operates through various segments, including Life Sciences, Diagnostics, Dental, and Environmental & Applied Solutions. Danaher's businesses are known for their innovation, quality, and customer service, and the company has a strong emphasis on continuous improvement and operational efficiency. Originally founded in 1984, Danaher has grown through a series of successful acquisitions and has established itself as a global leader in the industries it serves.

name: Salesforce
description: Salesforce, Inc. is an American cloud-based software company headquartered in San Francisco, California. It provides customer relationship management (CRM) software and other enterprise solutions to businesses of all sizes. Salesforce is known for its innovative approach to CRM, focusing on cloud technology and artificial intelligence to help companies manage their sales, customer service, marketing, and more. The company was founded in 1999 by former Oracle executive Marc Benioff and has since grown to become one of the largest and most well-known software companies in the world.

name: Paramount Global
description: Paramount Global is an American diversified multinational media conglomerate. The company was originally founded as Famous Players Film Company in 1912 and later became Paramount Pictures Corporation in 1916. Paramount Global operates as a major player in the entertainment industry, with interests in film production, television production, broadcasting, and streaming services. The company's portfolio includes Paramount Pictures, Paramount Television Studios, CBS Studios, Showtime Networks, and various other media assets. With a rich history in the entertainment business, Paramount Global continues to be a prominent and influential force in shaping popular culture worldwide.

name: CBRE Group
description: CBRE Group, Inc. is a commercial real estate services and investment firm. It is the largest commercial real estate services company in the world. CBRE offers a wide range of services, including property sales, leasing, property management, valuation, and mortgage services. The company operates in over 100 countries and has more than 100,000 employees worldwide. CBRE has been ranked as the top real estate investment firm for several years and is known for its expertise in the real estate market.

name: Micron Technology
description: Micron Technology, Inc. is an American producer of computer memory and computer data storage including dynamic random-access memory, flash memory, and USB flash drives. It is one of the largest memory manufacturers in the world and its products are used in a wide range of applications, from consumer electronics to enterprise servers. Micron Technology was founded in 1978 and has grown to become a leading player in the semiconductor industry.

name: Visa
description: Visa Inc. is an American multinational financial services corporation that facilitates electronic funds transfers throughout the world. It operates one of the world's largest payment processing networks, connecting consumers, businesses, financial institutions, and governments in more than 200 countries and territories. Visa enables digital payments and provides various financial services, including credit, debit, and prepaid cards. The company does not issue cards, extend credit, or set rates and fees for consumers; rather, it partners with financial institutions to offer Visa-branded payment products to their customers.

name: Southern Company
description: Southern Company is an American electric utility holding company based in the United States. It is one of the largest utility companies in the country, serving millions of customers in the Southeastern United States. Southern Company operates a range of energy-related businesses, including traditional and renewable electric utilities, natural gas distribution, and energy services. The company is known for its focus on innovation and sustainability in the energy sector.

name: United Natural Foods
description: United Natural Foods, Inc. (UNFI) is an American distributor of natural, organic, and specialty foods and non-food products. The company provides products to a wide range of customer locations, including natural product superstores, independent retailers, conventional supermarket chains, e-commerce retailers, and food service customers. UNFI has a focus on sustainability and social responsibility, aiming to provide healthier food options while also reducing its environmental impact. The company was founded in 1996 and has since grown to become a prominent distributor in the natural foods industry.

name: Paccar
description: PACCAR Inc is an American Fortune 500 company and a global technology leader in the design, manufacture, and customer support of high-quality light, medium, and heavy-duty trucks under the Kenworth, Peterbilt, Leyland Trucks, and DAF brands. PACCAR also designs and manufactures advanced diesel engines, provides financial services, information technology, and distributes truck parts related to its principal business. The company has a reputation for innovation, quality, and sustainability in the trucking industry.

name: Duke Energy
description: Duke Energy Corporation is an American utility company headquartered in the United States. It operates in the energy sector, specifically in electric power and natural gas distribution. Duke Energy serves millions of customers across several states, providing electricity and gas services. The company is known for its focus on renewable energy and sustainable practices, aiming to reduce its environmental impact. Duke Energy Corporation is a major player in the energy industry, with a significant presence in the market.

name: Eli Lilly
description: Eli Lilly and Company is an American pharmaceutical company headquartered in Indianapolis, Indiana. The company was founded in 1876 by Colonel Eli Lilly, a pharmaceutical chemist. Eli Lilly and Company is known for developing and manufacturing pharmaceutical drugs and medical devices across a range of therapeutic areas, including neuroscience, endocrinology, oncology, and immunology. The company is one of the largest pharmaceutical companies in the world and is particularly well-known for its production of insulin and other diabetes treatments. Eli Lilly and Company has a significant global presence and operates in numerous countries around the world.

name: Hewlett Packard Enterprise
description: Hewlett Packard Enterprise Company (HPE) is an American multinational enterprise information technology company. It was formed on November 1, 2015, following the split of the Hewlett-Packard Company into two separate entities: HP Inc. and HPE. HPE focuses on developing and providing a wide range of technology products, software, and services to businesses, government agencies, and educational institutions. Its offerings include servers, storage, networking, software, and consulting services. HPE is known for its innovation in areas such as edge computing, hybrid cloud solutions, and artificial intelligence. The company serves customers in various industries, including telecommunications, financial services, healthcare, and manufacturing.

name: Dollar Tree
description: Dollar Tree, Inc. is an American chain of discount variety stores that sells items for $1 or less. It operates more than 15,000 stores throughout the United States and Canada, offering a wide range of products including food and snacks, health and beauty products, household supplies, party supplies, toys, and more.
