It focuses on drug discovery, drug development, and vaccine technologies centered around messenger RNA (mRNA). The company was founded in 2010 and has gained international attention for its development of a COVID-19 vaccine, which has been authorized for emergency use in several countries. Moderna's mRNA technology platform is also being leveraged for the development of vaccines and therapeutics for various other infectious diseases, immuno-oncology, rare diseases, cardiovascular diseases, and autoimmune disorders.

name: DTE Energy
description: DTE Energy Company is a Detroit-based diversified energy company involved in the development and management of energy-related businesses and services nationwide. Its operating segments include electric, gas, and non-utility operations. The electric segment engages in the generation, purchase, distribution, and sale of electricity to approximately 2.2 million residential, commercial, and industrial customers in southeastern Michigan. The gas segment provides gas and gas-related services to over 1.3 million customers in Michigan. Additionally, the company operates non-utility segments involved in energy marketing and trading, and energy-related services. With a focus on sustainability and renewable energy, DTE Energy is committed to providing clean, safe, and reliable energy to its customers while also investing in environmental conservation and community initiatives.

name: Kinder Morgan
description: Kinder Morgan, Inc. is one of the largest energy infrastructure companies in North America. It specializes in owning and controlling oil and gas pipelines and terminals. The company operates approximately 84,000 miles of pipelines and 147 terminals across North America, handling various energy products such as natural gas, refined petroleum products, crude oil, carbon dioxide, and more. Kinder Morgan plays a crucial role in the transportation and storage of energy commodities, serving customers in both the United States and Canada.

name: Tenet Healthcare
description: Tenet Healthcare Corporation is a multinational healthcare services company based in the United States. It is one of the largest for-profit healthcare services providers in the nation, operating numerous hospitals, surgical centers, and outpatient facilities across the United States. Tenet Healthcare Corporation offers a wide range of healthcare services, including specialized medical treatment, emergency care, and diagnostic services. The company is committed to providing high-quality, compassionate care to patients and communities they serve.

name: Devon Energy
description: Devon Energy Corporation is an American independent energy company engaged in the exploration, development, and production of oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids. The company's operations are focused onshore in the United States, with a particular emphasis on the Permian Basin, the Eagle Ford Shale, the Anadarko Basin, and the Powder River Basin. Devon Energy is also involved in the transportation and marketing of oil, gas, and NGLs. The company was founded in 1971 and has grown to become one of the largest independent energy producers in the United States.

name: Mosaic
description: Mosaic ImmunoEngineering Inc. is a privately held biotechnology company that specializes in developing novel immunotherapies for cancer treatment. The company focuses on leveraging its proprietary technologies to engineer immune cells and create personalized cancer therapies that target and destroy tumors. Mosaic ImmunoEngineering Inc. aims to revolutionize cancer treatment by harnessing the power of the immune system to effectively combat various types of cancer.

name: Exelon
description: Exelon Corporation is an American Fortune 100 energy company headquartered in Chicago. It was created in October 2000 by the merger of PECO Energy Company and Unicom, which are two large electric utility companies. Exelon operates a variety of power plants, with a focus on nuclear power, as well as a growing renewable energy portfolio. The company serves customers in multiple states, providing electricity and natural gas to millions of customers. Exelon is also involved in energy trading and power marketing activities.

name: General Mills
description: General Mills, Inc. is an American multinational manufacturer and marketer of branded consumer foods sold through retail stores. It is headquartered in the United States. The company markets many well-known brands, such as Cheerios, Betty Crocker, Pillsbury, Haagen-Dazs, Yoplait, Nature Valley, and many others. General Mills is one of the world's largest food companies, with operations in more than 100 countries and employing over 35,000 people globally.

name: Global Partners
description: Global Partners LP is an American energy supply company that manages a network of gas stations, convenience stores, and terminals for storing and transporting petroleum and related products. The company, founded in 2005, operates predominantly in the northeastern United States. Global Partners LP also engages in the supply of gasoline, diesel, and home heating oil to wholesalers, retailers, and commercial customers. Additionally, the company owns and operates a fleet of transportation vehicles for delivering petroleum products and provides various services related to fuel distribution and logistics.

name: Western Digital
description: Western Digital Corporation is an American data storage company that designs, manufactures, and sells data technology products, including storage devices, data center systems, and cloud storage services. Founded in 1970, Western Digital is one of the largest computer hard disk drive manufacturers in the world. The company also produces solid-state drives, memory cards, and other data storage solutions for both personal and business use. In addition to its hardware products, Western Digital also provides software and services to help manage and protect data for a wide range of customers and industries.

name: Lincoln National
description: Lincoln National Corporation is a Fortune 250 American holding company, which operates multiple insurance and investment management businesses through its subsidiary companies. It was founded in Fort Wayne, Indiana, in 1905. The company offers a range of financial services, including life insurance, annuities, individual and group retirement plans, and wealth management services. Lincoln National Corporation is committed to helping individuals and families secure their financial futures through its various products and services.

name: Ross Stores
description: Ross Stores, Inc. is an American chain of off-price department stores that was founded in 1982 by Stuart Moldaw and Bill Isackson. The company operates under the name Ross Dress for Less and is headquartered in Pleasanton, California. Ross Stores offers a wide range of products including clothing, footwear, accessories, home goods, and beauty products at discounted prices. With over 1,500 stores in 39 states, Ross Stores is known for its "no frills" store layout and its focus on providing value to budget-conscious shoppers.

name: Stryker
description: Stryker Corporation is an American multinational medical technologies company that specializes in the design, production, and marketing of medical devices, equipment, and software solutions. The company's products are used in various medical specialties, including orthopedics, surgical, neurotechnology, and spine, among others. Stryker is known for its innovation in the healthcare industry and is a leading provider of medical technology worldwide.

name: Kyndryl Holdings
description: Kyndryl Holdings, Inc. is a global information technology company that provides technology and consulting services to businesses. It was established as an independent company following a spin-off from its former parent company. Kyndryl offers a range of services including IT infrastructure management, cloud services, cybersecurity, and digital transformation solutions to help businesses navigate the complexities of the digital world. The company serves clients in various industries, helping them optimize their IT operations and drive innovation.

name: Kohl's
description: Kohl's Corporation is an American department store retail chain, operating stores in every U.S. state except Hawaii. The company was founded by Maxwell Kohl in 1962. With a focus on affordable and fashionable clothing, household goods, and other merchandise, Kohl's has become a popular destination for shoppers across the country. In addition to its physical retail locations, Kohl's also sells its products online through its e-commerce platform.

name: Stanley Black & Decker
description: Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. is an American multinational corporation that specializes in manufacturing and distributing tools, hardware, and security products for professional, industrial, and consumer use. The company was formed in 2010 through the merger of Stanley Works and Black & Decker Corporation. Stanley Black & Decker is known for its wide range of well-known brands, including Stanley, DeWalt, Craftsman, and Black+Decker, among others. The company operates in three business segments: Tools and Storage, Industrial, and Security. Stanley Black & Decker is a Fortune 500 company and is one of the largest tool manufacturers in the world.

name: Colgate-Palmolive
description: Colgate-Palmolive Company is an American multinational consumer products company focused on the production, distribution, and provision of household, health care, and personal care products. The company was founded in 1806, originally as a soap and candle business, and has since grown to become a global leader in the industry. Colgate-Palmolive's product portfolio includes well-known brands such as Colgate toothpaste, Palmolive soap, Ajax cleaners, and Hill's Pet Nutrition. The company operates in over 200 countries worldwide and is committed to providing high-quality products that enhance health and well-being for consumers.

name: BlackRock
description: BlackRock, Inc. is an American global investment management corporation based in New York City. Founded in 1988, initially as a risk management and fixed income institutional asset manager, BlackRock is now the world's largest asset manager with over $8.67 trillion in assets under management as of January 2021. The company offers a wide range of financial products, including mutual funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), and other investment vehicles for institutional and individual investors worldwide. BlackRock is known for its expertise in risk management, investment research, and technology-driven solutions for its clients.

name: Fiserv
description: Fiserv, Inc. is an American multinational corporation that provides financial services technology. The company's services include payment processing for banks, credit unions, and other financial institutions, as well as account processing, electronic bill payment, and online banking services. Fiserv also offers software and services for mortgage and loan processing, risk management, and compliance. With operations in over 100 countries, Fiserv is a major player in the financial technology industry.

name: Estee Lauder
description: Estee Lauder Companies Inc. is an American multinational manufacturer and marketer of prestige skincare, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products. The company was founded in 1946 by Estee Lauder and her husband Joseph Lauder. Estee Lauder Companies operates multiple brands, including Estee Lauder, Clinique, MAC Cosmetics, Origins, Bobbi Brown, La Mer, Aveda, Jo Malone London, and many others. The company is known for its high-quality and innovative beauty products and has a global presence in over 150 countries.

name: PPG Industries
description: PPG Industries, Inc. is an American Fortune 500 company and global supplier of paints, coatings, and specialty materials. Founded in 1883 as Pittsburgh Plate Glass by Captain John B. Ford and John Pitcairn, Jr., the company is headquartered in the United States and operates in over 70 countries worldwide. PPG Industries is known for its innovation in developing coatings and materials for various industries, including automotive, aerospace, construction, and industrial applications. The company has a strong focus on sustainability and environmental responsibility, aiming to provide customers with high-quality products while minimizing its impact on the environment.

name: Adobe
description: Adobe Inc. is an American multinational computer software company headquartered in San Jose, California. It is best known for its Adobe Flash web software ecosystem, Photoshop image editing software, Adobe Illustrator vector graphics editor, Acrobat Reader, and the Portable Document Format (PDF). Adobe has historically focused upon the creation of multimedia and creativity software products, with a more recent foray towards digital marketing software. Adobe is the global leader in digital marketing and digital media solutions.

name: Block
description: Block, Inc. is an American technology company that specializes in online real estate services. It was founded in 2006 and its primary service is an online real estate marketplace for buying, selling, and renting properties. The company has developed innovative tools and features to streamline the real estate process for both buyers and sellers. In addition to its core real estate platform, Block, Inc. also offers related services such as property management and mortgage lending.

name: Synchrony Financial
description: Synchrony Financial is a consumer financial services company headquartered in the United States. It is one of the largest provider of private label credit cards in the United States based on purchase volume and receivables. The company offers a range of credit products through its various credit programs including retail credit, promotional financing, and installment lending for major industries such as retail, healthcare, and home furnishings. Synchrony Financial also provides online banking services, and its offerings include deposit products, high-yield savings accounts, and certificates of deposit.

name: Principal Financial
description: Principal Financial Group, Inc. is a global financial services company headquartered in the United States. The company offers a wide range of financial products and services, including retirement solutions, insurance, and investment management. With a focus on helping individuals and businesses achieve financial security and success, Principal Financial Group has established itself as a leading provider in the financial services industry. The company has a strong presence both domestically and internationally, serving millions of customers worldwide.

name: Lumen Technologies
description: Lumen Technologies, Inc. is an American telecommunications company that offers a range of services including data and internet protocol services, cloud, voice, and managed services. The company was formerly known as CenturyLink, Inc. before rebranding as Lumen Technologies in September 2021. Lumen Technologies serves customers in more than 60 countries and has a global fiber network that spans over 450,000 route miles. The company is focused on providing solutions for businesses, government agencies, and consumers to help them manage and secure their data and digital assets.

name: Corteva
description: Corteva, Inc. is a leading American agricultural chemical and seed company that was founded in 2019 as a result of the spinoff of the agricultural division of DowDuPont. The company focuses on providing farmers around the world with innovative solutions and products to increase crop yields and profitability, while also promoting sustainable agricultural practices. Corteva produces a wide range of crop protection products, hybrid seeds, and digital agriculture tools to help farmers meet the growing demand for food in a sustainable way.

name: Andersons
description: The Andersons, Inc. is a diversified company with businesses in the agriculture, plant nutrient, ethanol, and rail sectors. The company was founded in Maumee, Ohio, in 1947. The Andersons operates grain elevators, conducts wholesale and retail sales of fertilizer and other agricultural products, produces ethanol, and offers railcar repair services. With over 70 locations across the United States, The Andersons serves customers in the agricultural and transportation industries.

name: Lam Research
description: Lam Research Corporation is an American corporation that engages in the design, manufacture, marketing, and service of semiconductor processing equipment used in the fabrication of integrated circuits. Its products are primarily used in front-end wafer processing, which includes thin film deposition, plasma etch, photoresist strip, and wafer cleaning. Lam Research Corporation was founded in 1980 and has since grown to become a leading supplier of wafer fabrication equipment and services to the global semiconductor industry.

name: Edison International
description: Edison International is a public utility holding company based in the United States. It is dedicated to providing electric power and energy services to communities in both the United States and abroad. Edison International operates through its subsidiaries, which include Southern California Edison (SCE) and Edison Energy Group. SCE is a utility company that serves a majority of Southern California's population, delivering electricity to more than 15 million people. Additionally, Edison Energy Group focuses on providing energy consulting services and distributed energy solutions to commercial and industrial customers. Edison International is committed to promoting sustainability and advancing clean energy initiatives while delivering reliable and affordable energy to its customers.

name: Dominion Energy
description: Dominion Energy, Inc. is an American power and energy company headquartered in Richmond, Virginia. It is one of the nation's largest producers and transporters of energy, with a portfolio of natural gas and electric businesses serving customers in 18 states. Dominion Energy was founded in the early 20th century and has since grown into a major player in the energy sector, providing electricity and natural gas to millions of customers. The company is also committed to sustainability and investing in renewable energy sources to reduce its environmental impact.

name: Booking Holdings
description: Booking Holdings Inc. is an American company that owns and operates several travel fare aggregators and travel metasearch engines, including Booking.com, Priceline.com, Agoda.com, Kayak.com, Cheapflights, Rentalcars.com, Momondo, and OpenTable. Booking Holdings is a publicly traded company on the NASDAQ stock exchange. The company is known for providing online booking services for hotels, flights, car rentals, and restaurant reservations worldwide.

name: Quanta Services
description: Quanta Services, Inc. is a U.S.-based corporation that provides specialty contracting services for electrical power infrastructure, natural gas and oil pipeline, and telecommunications. The company operates in North America, Australia, and other select international markets, offering a wide range of services including design, installation, maintenance, and repair for various infrastructure projects. Quanta Services is known for its expertise in delivering comprehensive solutions for complex energy and communications infrastructure challenges.

name: Expeditors Intl. of Washington
description: Expeditors International of Washington, Inc. is a global logistics and freight forwarding company headquartered in Seattle, Washington. The company offers supply chain solutions, including air and ocean freight consolidation and forwarding, customs brokerage, vendor consolidation, cargo insurance, purchase order management, and distribution. Expeditors operates a network of over 300 locations across six continents, providing services to a wide range of industries, including aerospace, consumer retail, healthcare, technology, and more. Established in 1979, Expeditors has grown to become a leading player in the logistics industry, known for its efficient and dependable services.

name: L3Harris Technologies
description: L3Harris Technologies, Inc. is an American technology company that provides communication systems and products, as well as defense and aerospace systems. The company was formed in 2019 through the merger of L3 Technologies and Harris Corporation. L3Harris Technologies serves customers in the defense, government, commercial, and industrial markets with a wide range of products and services, including electronic warfare, avionics, surveillance and reconnaissance systems, and satellite communications.

name: Reliance Steel & Aluminum
description: Reliance Steel & Aluminum Co. is a metals service center company in North America. It provides metals processing services and distributes a wide range of metal products, including alloy, aluminum, brass, copper, carbon steel, stainless steel, and titanium. The company serves a variety of industries, such as aerospace, defense, energy, transportation, and fabrication. Reliance Steel & Aluminum Co. operates in over 300 locations across the United States, Canada, and Mexico, and has been in operation for over 80 years.

name: Live Nation Entertainment
description: Live Nation Entertainment, Inc. is an American global entertainment company that was founded in 2010 through the merger of Live Nation and Ticketmaster. The company is involved in the production of music concerts, organization of events, and management of artists. Live Nation Entertainment is one of the largest live entertainment companies in the world, with a significant presence in the concert promotion and ticketing industries. The company operates in multiple segments, including concerts, ticketing, sponsorship and advertising, and artist management. Live Nation Entertainment is known for its extensive network of venues and events worldwide.

name: DISH Network
description: DISH Network Corporation is a leading provider of satellite television, internet, and other digital entertainment services in the United States. The company was founded in 1980 and has since grown to become one of the largest pay-TV providers in the country, serving millions of customers with a wide range of programming options. DISH Network offers a variety of packages that include hundreds of channels, on-demand content, and access to popular streaming services. In addition to its television services, the company also provides high-speed internet and home automation solutions to residential and commercial customers. DISH Network is known for its innovative technology, competitive pricing, and commitment to customer satisfaction.

name: DuPont
description: DuPont de Nemours, Inc., commonly known as DuPont, is an American company that was founded in 1802 as a gunpowder mill. Over the years, DuPont has evolved into a multinational conglomerate with business interests in a wide range of industries including agriculture, materials science, and biotechnology. The company is known for its innovative products and technologies, particularly in the areas of chemicals, electronics, and safety equipment. DuPont has a long history of research and development, and has been responsible for many groundbreaking inventions and discoveries throughout its existence.

name: Automatic Data Processing
description: Automatic Data Processing, Inc. (ADP) is an American provider of human resources management software and services. It is one of the largest human resources companies in the world, offering services such as payroll processing, time and attendance management, benefits administration, and compliance solutions. ADP serves over 810,000 clients in more than 140 countries and has operations in North America, Europe, Latin America, and the Asia-Pacific region. The company was founded in 1949 and is headquartered in the United States.

name: Group 1 Automotive
description: Group 1 Automotive, Inc. is an international Fortune 500 automotive retailer with locations in the United States, the United Kingdom, and Brazil. The company is one of the largest automotive dealership groups in the United States, with over 180 dealerships representing 33 brands. Group 1 Automotive, Inc. offers a wide range of automotive products and services, including new and used vehicles, vehicle parts, maintenance and repair services, and financing and insurance products. The company is known for its commitment to customer service and has received numerous awards for its performance and dedication to excellence in the automotive industry.

name: Aramark
description: Aramark Corporation is an American food service, facilities, and uniform services provider to clients in various industries, including education, healthcare, business, corrections, and leisure. With a global presence, Aramark operates in over 20 countries and serves millions of customers daily. The company offers services such as dining, catering, facility management, and uniform provision to a diverse range of clients, including corporations, schools, stadiums, and hospitals. Aramark is known for its focus on sustainability and social responsibility in its operations.

name: Thor Industries
description: Thor Industries, Inc. is an American manufacturer of recreational vehicles (RVs). The company was founded in 1980 and has since grown to become one of the largest RV manufacturers in the world. Thor Industries produces a wide range of RVs, including motorhomes, travel trailers, and fifth-wheel trailers, under several brand names. The company has manufacturing facilities across North America and sells its products through a network of dealers in the United States and internationally. Thor Industries is known for its innovation, quality, and diverse product offerings in the RV industry.

name: DXC Technology
description: DXC Technology Company is an American multinational corporation that provides information technology services and solutions. It was formed through the merger of Computer Sciences Corporation (CSC) and the Enterprise Services business of Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE). DXC Technology offers a wide range of services including consulting, analytics, enterprise applications, cloud services, and cybersecurity. The company serves various industries including healthcare, financial services, manufacturing, and the public sector. With a global presence, DXC Technology employs thousands of professionals worldwide to help companies modernize their IT infrastructure and navigate digital transformation.

name: Viatris
description: Viatris Inc. is an American pharmaceutical company formed in 2020 through a merger of Mylan and Upjohn, a division of Pfizer. The company is headquartered in the United States and specializes in the development, manufacturing, and distribution of generic and specialty pharmaceuticals, as well as over-the-counter (OTC) products. Viatris operates in over 165 countries and territories worldwide, with a focus on providing access to affordable healthcare solutions.

name: Reinsurance Group of America
description: Reinsurance Group of America, Incorporated (RGA) is a leading global life and health reinsurance company with operations in more than 60 countries. The company offers individual and group life and health-related reinsurance solutions to insurance companies worldwide. RGA was founded in 1973 and has since grown to become one of the largest reinsurance companies in the world. The company is known for its expertise in risk management, underwriting, and actuarial services, as well as its innovation in developing reinsurance solutions tailored to meet the unique needs of its clients.

name: AutoZone
description: AutoZone, Inc. is an American retailer of aftermarket automotive parts and accessories, including automotive hard parts, maintenance items, accessories, and non-automotive products. Founded in 1979, AutoZone has over 6,000 stores across the United States, Mexico, Brazil, and Puerto Rico. With a focus on providing its customers with the parts they need to fix their vehicles, AutoZone also offers services such as free engine code scanning, battery charging, and oil recycling.

name: PulteGroup
description: PulteGroup, Inc. is a home construction company founded in 1950 by Bill Pulte. It is one of the largest home construction companies in the United States, operating in 44 markets across the country. PulteGroup primarily focuses on constructing and selling single-family homes, townhouses, and condominiums. The company is known for its energy-efficient and environmentally friendly building practices. PulteGroup has multiple brands under its umbrella, including Pulte Homes, Centex, Del Webb, DiVosta, and John Wieland Homes and Neighborhoods.

name: Illinois Tool Works
description: Illinois Tool Works Inc. (ITW) is an American Fortune 200 global manufacturer of engineered products and specialty systems. The company operates through seven segments: Automotive OEM, Test & Measurement and Electronics, Food Equipment, Polymers & Fluids, Welding, Construction Products, and Specialty Products. ITW has a diversified business portfolio with a strong focus on innovation, customer-centric solutions, and operational excellence. The company was founded in 1912 and has a long-standing history of providing value-added products and services to customers across various industries worldwide.

name: Parker-Hannifin
description: Parker-Hannifin Corporation is an American corporation specializing in motion and control technologies. It was founded in 1917 and is headquartered in the United States. The company operates in the manufacturing and engineering sectors, providing a wide range of products and systems used in various industries such as aerospace, industrial, and automotive. Parker-Hannifin Corporation is known for its expertise in motion and control technologies, including hydraulics, pneumatics, electromechanical, filtration, and fluid connectors. The company has a global presence with operations in numerous countries around the world.

name: BorgWarner
description: BorgWarner Inc. is an American global automotive supplier headquartered in the United States. The company focuses on powertrain components and systems for combustion, hybrid, and electric vehicles. They specialize in technologies to improve fuel efficiency, emissions, and performance in a wide range of vehicles. BorgWarner operates manufacturing and technical facilities around the world and serves customers in over 60 countries.

name: Westlake
description: Westlake Chemical Partners LP is a company that was formed by Westlake Chemical Corporation in 2014. It is a limited partnership that is engaged in the acquisition, development, operation, and maintenance of ethylene production facilities. As a subsidiary of Westlake Chemical Corporation, Westlake Chemical Partners LP operates ethylene production facilities in the United States. The company's operations primarily involve the production of ethylene, which is a key building block used in the petrochemical industry for the production of a wide range of consumer and industrial products.

name: Consolidated Edison
description: Consolidated Edison, Inc., commonly known as Con Edison, is one of the largest investor-owned energy companies in the United States. It provides a wide range of energy-related products and services to its customers in New York City and Westchester County. Con Edison is primarily involved in the transmission and distribution of electricity and natural gas. The company also operates renewable energy projects and offers energy efficiency programs to promote sustainability and reduce environmental impact. Con Edison has a long history dating back to the 19th century and has played a crucial role in powering the growth and development of New York City.

name: Gap
description: The Gap, Inc. is an American worldwide clothing and accessories retailer. The company was founded in 1969 by Donald Fisher and Doris F. Fisher and has since grown to become one of the world's largest specialty retailers. The Gap operates several well-known brands, including Gap, Old Navy, Banana Republic, Athleta, and Intermix. The company is known for its casual clothing and accessories for men, women, and children, as well as its commitment to sustainability and social responsibility.

name: Opendoor Technologies
description: Opendoor Technologies Inc. is an American real estate technology company that operates an online marketplace for buying and selling homes. The company utilizes technology to streamline the real estate transaction process, allowing homeowners to sell their properties quickly and conveniently. Opendoor was founded in 2014 and has since grown to become a significant player in the real estate industry, providing an alternative to traditional home buying and selling methods.

name: Nordstrom
description: Nordstrom, Inc. is an American luxury department store chain founded in 1901 by John W. Nordstrom and Carl F. Wallin. Nordstrom operates multiple retail formats, including its flagship Nordstrom stores, Nordstrom Rack, and concept stores such as Nordstrom Local. The company offers a wide range of high-end fashion apparel, shoes, accessories, and beauty products from various brands. Known for its exceptional customer service and upscale shopping experience, Nordstrom has established itself as a prominent retailer in the fashion industry.

name: Asbury Automotive Group
description: Asbury Automotive Group, Inc. is an American automotive retail and service company. It is one of the largest automotive retailers in the United States, with over 80 dealerships across various states. The company sells new and used vehicles, offers vehicle maintenance and repair services, as well as sells automotive parts and accessories. Asbury Automotive Group, Inc. represents multiple automotive brands and has a significant presence in the automotive retail industry.

name: Ball
description: Ball Corporation is an American company headquartered in Broomfield, Colorado. It is best known for its production of metal packaging, primarily for beverages and food, as well as aerospace and other technologies and services. Ball Corporation was founded in 1880 by five brothers as a manufacturer of tin cans. Over the years, the company has expanded its product offerings and global presence. Today, Ball Corporation is a leading supplier of sustainable packaging solutions and aerospace technology.

name: Kellogg
description: The Kellogg Company is an American multinational food manufacturing company that produces cereal and convenience foods, including cookies, crackers, and toaster pastries. The company's brands include Kellogg's, Keebler, Pringles, Eggo, Cheez-It, and Morningstar Farms. Kellogg's mission is to nourish families so they can flourish and thrive. The company was founded in 1906 by Will Keith Kellogg and is headquartered in Battle Creek, Michigan.

name: Xcel Energy
description: Xcel Energy Inc. is a large utility holding company based in the United States. It provides electricity and natural gas services to customers in eight states, including Colorado, Michigan, Minnesota, New Mexico, North Dakota, South Dakota, Texas, and Wisconsin. Xcel Energy is known for its focus on renewable energy and has been a leader in wind and solar power generation. The company serves millions of customers and is committed to providing safe, reliable, and clean energy solutions.

name: W.W. Grainger
description: W.W. Grainger, Inc. is an American Fortune 500 industrial supply company founded in 1927. It is a distributor of maintenance, repair, and operating (MRO) products, with operations primarily in North America, Europe, and Asia. Grainger serves more than 3 million customers worldwide and offers a wide range of products including electrical and lighting supplies, power tools, safety equipment, and janitorial supplies. The company also provides inventory management and technical support services to help businesses streamline their procurement processes.

name: Discover Financial Services
description:
Discover Financial Services is an American financial services company that operates as a direct banking and payment services company. It is known for its credit card line, which includes the Discover Card, and its various banking products such as savings accounts, certificates of deposit, and personal loans. Discover also offers payment processing services for merchants and cash access at ATMs.
Discover is one of the largest card issuers in the United States and is known for its customer-friendly approach and innovative services, such as cashback rewards and no annual fees on many of its products. The company was founded in 1985 and has since grown to become a prominent player in the financial services industry.

name: Baxter International
description: Baxter International Inc. is an American multinational healthcare company that develops, manufactures, and markets products for people with hemophilia, immune disorders, infectious diseases, kidney disease, trauma, and other chronic medical conditions. The company also provides products and services for healthcare providers, including pharmacy compounding, drug formulation services, and intravenous (IV) nutrition. Baxter International Inc. is known for its innovative medical technologies and has a focus on advancing patient care around the world.

name: Southwestern Energy
description: Southwestern Energy Company is an American energy company primarily engaged in natural gas and oil exploration, production, and marketing. The company was founded in 1929 and has grown to become a prominent player in the energy industry. Southwestern Energy Company operates in various basins in the United States, including the Appalachian Basin and the Arkoma Basin. The company is known for its focus on utilizing innovative technologies and sustainable practices in its operations to efficiently extract natural resources while minimizing environmental impact.

name: DCP Midstream
description: DCP Midstream, LP is a Fortune 500 company that specializes in natural gas liquids (NGLs) and crude oil logistics, marketing, gathering, and processing. The company operates across the United States, with a focus on the development of energy infrastructure and the transportation of energy products. DCP Midstream, LP is known for its strategic partnerships with leading energy companies and its commitment to innovation in the energy sector.

name: Jacobs Solutions
description: Jacobs Solutions Inc. is an American publicly traded company that provides professional technical services, including engineering, design, architecture, construction, operations, and maintenance. Jacobs Solutions Inc. serves various industries, including aerospace, defense, environmental, infrastructure, and petrochemical sectors. The company operates globally and has a diverse range of clients in both the public and private sectors. Their services range from consulting to project management and implementation, with a focus on sustainability and innovation.

name: Laboratory Corp. of America
industry: Health Care: Pharmacy and Other Services
description: Laboratory Corporation of America Holdings, commonly known as LabCorp, is an American company engaged in the business of clinical laboratory services. It is one of the largest clinical laboratory networks in the world, with a broad range of testing capabilities and diagnostic services that are used by healthcare professionals, pharmaceutical companies, and patients. LabCorp offers a comprehensive menu of laboratory tests and services, including blood tests, urinalysis, genetic testing, and infectious disease testing. The company plays a crucial role in the healthcare industry by providing accurate and timely test results to aid in the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of diseases.

name: CSX
description: CSX Corporation is an American holding company focused on rail transportation and real estate in North America. The company was formed in 1980 through the merger of Chessie System and Seaboard Coast Line Industries. CSX operates a Class I railroad in the eastern United States with a network that serves major markets in the Midwest and Southeast. With a history dating back to 1915, Commercial Metals Company has grown to become a leading player in the steel industry, providing a wide range of products and services to customers in various sectors, including construction, infrastructure, manufacturing, and energy. The company is known for its commitment to sustainability and environmental stewardship through its recycling operations and efforts to reduce its carbon footprint.

name: Autoliv
description: Autoliv, Inc. is a Swedish-American company that specializes in automotive safety systems. It is the world's largest automotive safety supplier, developing and manufacturing airbags, seatbelts, steering wheels, and other safety components for major automobile manufacturers across the globe. Autoliv was founded in 1953 and has since expanded its operations internationally, employing over 67,000 people in more than 27 countries. The company is focused on developing innovative safety technology to protect passengers in vehicles and reduce the number of traffic accidents worldwide.

name: Constellation Brands
description: Constellation Brands, Inc. is an American diversified beverage company with a portfolio of well-known and globally recognized beer, wine, and spirits brands. The company was established in 1945 and has since grown to become one of the leading alcohol producers in the United States. Constellation Brands owns and markets a wide range of popular brands across different categories, including beer brands such as Corona, Modelo, and Pacifico, wine brands such as Robert Mondavi, Kim Crawford, and Meiomi, as well as spirits brands like Svedka Vodka and High West Whiskey.

name: Hilton Worldwide Holdings
description: Hilton Worldwide Holdings Inc. is an American multinational hospitality company that manages and franchises a broad portfolio of hotels and resorts. Founded by Conrad Hilton in 1919, it is one of the largest and fastest-growing hospitality companies in the world. Hilton's portfolio includes a wide range of hotel brands catering to different market segments, including luxury, full-service, select-service, and extended-stay properties. With a global presence spanning over 100 countries, Hilton is known for its high standards of hospitality and customer service.

name: Foot Locker
description: Foot Locker, Inc. is an American sportswear and footwear retailer that operates in approximately 20 countries worldwide. The company was established in 1974 and is known for its wide selection of athletic footwear, apparel, and accessories from popular brands such as Nike, Adidas, Jordan, and Puma. Foot Locker, Inc. operates multiple retail chains, including Foot Locker, Kids Foot Locker, Champs Sports, and Eastbay, catering to a diverse customer base of athletes and sneaker enthusiasts.

name: Huntsman
description: Huntsman Corporation is an American multinational manufacturer and marketer of chemical products for consumers and industrial customers. The company operates in four business segments: Polyurethanes, Performance Products, Advanced Materials, and Textile Effects. Huntsman Corporation was founded in 1970 and has grown to become a leading global specialty chemicals company, with a focus on innovation and sustainability in its products and processes.

name: Burlington Stores
description: Burlington Stores, Inc., commonly known as Burlington, is an American national off-price department store retailer. It was founded in 1972 and has over 750 stores in 40 states and Puerto Rico. Burlington offers a wide range of products including clothing, shoes, accessories, furniture, and home goods from various brands at discounted prices. It is known for providing high-quality merchandise at affordable prices, making it a popular destination for budget-conscious shoppers.

name: Hertz Global Holdings
description: Hertz Global Holdings, Inc. is an American car rental company that operates through its Hertz, Dollar, Thrifty, and Firefly brands. The company is one of the largest car rental companies in the world, with locations in 150 countries. Hertz was founded in 1918 and is headquartered in Estero, Florida. The company offers a wide range of rental vehicles, including cars, trucks, vans, and SUVs, to both leisure and business customers. In addition to its car rental services, Hertz also provides fleet management and car sales services.

name: Masco
description: Masco Corporation is a global manufacturer of home improvement and building products. The company was founded in 1929 and has grown to become one of the leading providers of branded products for the home improvement and new home construction markets. Masco's product portfolio includes faucets, cabinets, architectural coatings, windows, and other related products. The company operates through various subsidiaries and has a presence in North America, Europe, and other international markets. With a focus on innovation and quality, Masco Corporation aims to enhance the overall living experience for consumers around the world.

name: Williams-Sonoma
description: Williams-Sonoma, Inc. is an American publicly traded consumer retail company that sells kitchenware and home furnishings. It was founded in 1956 by Charles E. Williams in Sonoma, California. The company operates several retail brands, including its namesake Williams Sonoma, Pottery Barn, Pottery Barn Kids, West Elm, and others. Williams-Sonoma, Inc. is known for its high-quality products, upscale image, and focus on customer service.

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
description: Chipotle Mexican Grill, Inc. is an American chain of fast-casual restaurants specializing in tacos and Mission-style burritos. The company is known for its focus on using high-quality, sustainably sourced ingredients in its dishes. Chipotle was founded in 1993 by Steve Ells and has since grown to become a popular dining option for customers seeking fresh, customizable Mexican-inspired food. The company is committed to food transparency and has implemented initiatives to promote ethically sourced ingredients and environmentally friendly practices.

name: M&T Bank
description: M&T Bank Corporation is an American bank holding company that was founded in 1856. It is based in the United States and is one of the 20 largest commercial bank holding companies in the country. M&T Bank offers a range of financial products and services to its customers, including retail and commercial banking, wealth management, and investment services. The bank operates over 750 branches and more than 1,800 ATMs in states such as New York, Maryland, New Jersey, Pennsylvania, Delaware, Connecticut, Virginia, West Virginia, and the District of Columbia.

name: LPL Financial Holdings
description: LPL Financial Holdings Inc. is a publicly traded financial services company that was founded in 1989. The company provides brokerage, investment advisory, and other financial services to independent financial advisors, financial institutions, and individual investors in the United States. LPL Financial is one of the largest organizations of independent financial advisors in the country and has a network of over 17,000 financial advisors. The company is headquartered in the United States and offers a wide range of services and resources to help clients achieve their financial goals.

name: CMS Energy
description: CMS Energy Corporation is a public utility holding company based in the United States. It is the parent company of Consumers Energy, a natural gas and electric utility serving Michigan. CMS Energy Corporation was founded in 1987 and is listed on the New York Stock Exchange. The company is involved in the generation, transmission, and distribution of electricity, as well as natural gas operations. CMS Energy Corporation is committed to providing reliable and sustainable energy to its customers while focusing on clean energy initiatives and environmental stewardship.

name: Campbell Soup
description: Campbell Soup Company, also known as Campbell's, is an American multinational food company that specializes in the production and distribution of canned soups and related products. Established in 1869 by Joseph A. Campbell and Abraham Anderson, the company has since expanded its product line to include broths, condensed soups, cookies, crackers, and beverages. Campbell's iconic red and white cans of soup have become a staple in households across the United States and beyond. In addition to its namesake brand, Campbell Soup Company owns and operates several other popular food brands.

name: Arthur J. Gallagher
description: Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. is a global insurance brokerage and risk management services firm headquartered in the United States. The company offers a range of services, including commercial brokerage, risk management, and human resource consulting. Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. operates in various industries, such as aerospace, construction, energy, healthcare, and transportation. With a strong presence in the insurance industry, the company serves clients worldwide and has grown through acquisitions and strategic partnerships.

name: Blackstone
description: Blackstone Inc. is an American multinational private equity alternative investment management company. It was founded in 1985 by a group of former employees of Lehman Brothers and specializes in private equity, credit, and hedge fund investment strategies. Blackstone is one of the largest investment firms in the world and manages a wide range of assets including private equity, real estate, credit, and hedge funds. The company is headquartered in New York City and has offices in major cities around the world.

name: Dover
description: Dover Corporation is an American conglomerate manufacturer of industrial products. Founded in 1955, the company operates in four business segments: Engineered Systems, Fluids, Refrigeration & Food Equipment, and Energy. Dover serves a wide range of industries including electronics, chemicals, energy, food and beverage, retail, and more. The company is known for its diverse portfolio of products and services, innovative solutions, and global presence.

name: ODP
description: The ODP Corporation is a retail company that offers business services and supplies through multiple channels, including online, retail stores, direct sales, and catalogs. Formerly known as Office Depot, Inc., the company rebranded as The ODP Corporation in 2021. The company provides office products, technology products, furniture, supplies, print and document services, and other business services to customers ranging from individuals to large corporations. With a focus on helping businesses succeed, The ODP Corporation aims to provide innovative and sustainable solutions to meet the evolving needs of its customers.

name: Packaging Corp. of America
description: Packaging Corporation of America (PCA) is an American packaging and paper company that specializes in producing corrugated packaging products, containerboard, and uncoated papers. With over 140 facilities across the United States, the company offers a wide range of packaging solutions for various industries, including food and beverage, e-commerce, consumer goods, and industrial products. PCA is known for its sustainable practices and commitment to environmental stewardship through initiatives such as responsible forestry management and energy efficiency.

name: Brighthouse Financial
description: Brighthouse Financial, Inc. is a leading provider of annuities and life insurance in the United States. The company was established in 2016 as a spin-off from MetLife. Brighthouse Financial offers a range of products designed to help individuals and families achieve financial security and prepare for retirement. They focus on helping customers create a protected income that can last a lifetime, as well as providing solutions for long-term care planning. In addition to their products, Brighthouse Financial also offers educational resources and tools to help individuals make informed decisions about their financial futures.

name: Beacon Roofing Supply
description: Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. is an American publicly traded company that distributes residential and non-residential roofing materials, as well as complementary building products. The company was founded in 1928 and has since grown to become one of the largest distributors of roofing materials in the United States. Beacon Roofing operates over 400 branches across North America and offers a wide range of products including shingles, metal roofing, and waterproofing materials.

name: Airbnb
description: Airbnb, Inc. is an American online marketplace company based in San Francisco, California. It was founded in 2008 by Brian Chesky, Joe Gebbia, and Nathan Blecharczyk, and operates a platform for individuals to rent out their properties for short-term lodging. Users can book accommodations through the Airbnb website or mobile app, connecting hosts with travelers looking for unique and local lodging options. The company has grown to become one of the largest accommodation sharing platforms globally, offering a wide range of housing options, from apartments and vacation homes to unique properties like castles and treehouses.

name: Boise Cascade
description: Boise Cascade Company is an American pulp and paper company that produces wood products and owns timberland in the United States. The company manufactures a wide range of products including lumber, plywood, particleboard, and engineered wood products. Boise Cascade also operates distribution facilities that supply building materials such as lumber, siding, decking, and insulation. The company has a long history dating back to the early 20th century and has grown to become a major player in the forest products industry in the United States.

name: Booz Allen Hamilton Holding
description: Booz Allen Hamilton Holding Corporation is the parent company of Booz Allen Hamilton Inc., an American management and information technology consulting firm. The company provides consulting services to a wide range of clients, including government agencies, corporations, and non-profit organizations. Booz Allen Hamilton is known for its expertise in areas such as cybersecurity, technology integration, strategic consulting, and analytics. The company was founded in 1914 and has grown to become one of the leading consulting firms in the United States.

name: Westinghouse Air Brake Technologies
description: Westinghouse Air Brake Technologies Corporation, commonly known as Wabtec, is an American company that provides equipment, systems, and services for the global rail industry. The company manufactures a wide range of products for locomotives, freight cars, and passenger transit vehicles, including brakes, electronics, air compressors, and more. Wabtec also offers train control and signaling solutions, as well as a variety of aftermarket services to support the maintenance and operation of rail systems. With a history dating back to the 19th century, Wabtec is a leading provider of innovative technology and solutions for the transportation industry.

name: ON Semiconductor
description: ON Semiconductor Corporation is a leading American semiconductor supplier company that designs and manufactures a wide range of power and signal management, logic, discrete, and custom devices for automotive, communications, computing, consumer, industrial, and medical applications. The company was originally founded in 1999 and has since grown to become a key player in the global semiconductor industry. ON Semiconductor is known for its innovative solutions in energy-efficient electronics and power management technologies.

name: Oshkosh
description: Oshkosh Corporation, formerly Oshkosh Truck, is an American industrial company that designs and builds specialty trucks, military vehicles, truck bodies, airport fire apparatus, and access equipment. The company was founded in 1917 in Oshkosh, Wisconsin and has since grown into a global leader in the manufacturing of specialty vehicles for various industries, including defense, transportation, construction, and firefighting. Oshkosh Corporation is known for its innovation, quality, and commitment to providing reliable and durable vehicles for its customers worldwide.

name: Franklin Resources
description: Franklin Resources, Inc., is an American multinational holding company specializing in asset management. It is the parent company of Franklin Templeton Investments, a global investment management organization known for its range of mutual funds, investment strategies, and wealth management services. Franklin Resources, Inc., was founded in 1947 by Rupert H. Johnson, Sr., and is headquartered in San Mateo, California. The company operates in over 30 countries and serves clients worldwide, managing assets across equity, fixed income, multi-asset, and alternative strategies.

name: Taylor Morrison Home
description: Taylor Morrison Home Corporation is a home construction company in the United States. The company operates in multiple states across the U.S. and is known for its focus on innovation, quality craftsmanship, and customer satisfaction. Taylor Morrison Home Corporation has a long history in the homebuilding industry and has established itself as a leading player in the market.

name: A-Mark Precious Metals

The company offers a variety of services, such as financing, storage, logistics, and other resources to its customers. A-Mark serves various industries, including coin dealers, jewelers, investors, and collectors worldwide. The company was founded in 1965 and has since become a prominent player in the precious metals industry.

KeyCorp operates through its primary subsidiary, KeyBank National Association, offering a wide range of retail and commercial banking, investment management, and mortgage lending services to individuals, businesses, and institutional clients. The company traces its history back to 1825 and has grown through mergers and acquisitions to become a significant player in the financial services industry.

name: ARKO

The company was founded in the mid-20th century and has since grown to become a key player in the business world. Arko Corp has a diverse portfolio of investments and is known for its strategic approach to business expansion and development. The company has a strong track record of success and continues to explore new opportunities for growth and innovation in the market.

name: Lululemon athletica
description: Lululemon Athletica Inc., styled as lululemon athletica, is a Canadian athletic apparel retailer founded in 1998. The company sells athletic wear including tops, bottoms, and accessories for yoga, running, and other active pursuits. Lululemon is known for its high-quality, stylish activewear and has developed a strong following among fitness enthusiasts and athleisure fans. The brand emphasizes a healthy lifestyle and community engagement, often hosting events and classes in its stores.

name: Old Republic International
description: Old Republic International Corporation is an American insurance company that focuses on providing various types of insurance coverage, including property and liability insurance, as well as title and mortgage insurance. The company was founded in 1923 and has since grown to become a prominent player in the insurance industry. Old Republic International Corporation operates through various subsidiaries, each specializing in different aspects of the insurance market. The company is known for its long-standing presence in the industry and its commitment to providing reliable insurance products and services to its customers.

name: Zoetis

It was established in 2013 as a spin-off of Pfizer's animal health division. Zoetis Inc. is one of the largest veterinary pharmaceutical companies in the world, offering a wide range of products to support the health and well-being of animals. The company is dedicated to providing innovative solutions to veterinarians, livestock producers, and pet owners to help ensure the health and safety of animals worldwide.

name: Marathon Oil
description: Marathon Oil Corporation is an American independent energy company engaged in the exploration, production, and marketing of oil and natural gas resources. With operations primarily in the United States, Equatorial Guinea, and the United Kingdom, Marathon Oil is involved in various aspects of the energy industry, including the development of oil and gas reserves, as well as the refining and marketing of petroleum products. The company has a history dating back to the early 20th century and has evolved into a prominent player in the global energy sector.

name: J.M. Smucker
description: The J.M. Smucker Company, commonly known as Smucker's, is an American manufacturer of fruit spreads, ice cream toppings, beverages, shortening, peanut butter, and other products in North America. The company was founded in 1897 by Jerome Monroe Smucker and is headquartered in the United States. Smucker's is known for its iconic fruit preserves and spreads, as well as its strong presence in the coffee and pet food markets. Today, the company has grown to become a leading player in the food and beverage industry, with a wide range of products under its portfolio.

name: Huntington Bancshares

It is the parent company of Huntington National Bank, which operates over 1,000 branches and maintains a network of ATMs across several states. The company offers a range of banking and financial services, including personal, business, and commercial banking, as well as wealth management and insurance products. Huntington Bancshares is known for its community involvement and commitment to customer service.

name: NGL Energy Partners

The company also offers water treatment and disposal services for the oil and gas industry. NGL Energy Partners LP is headquartered in the United States and operates a network of facilities across North America.

name: Ingredion

The company operates globally and serves customers in over 120 countries. Ingredion's products are used in a wide range of applications, such as enhancing texture, taste, and nutritional value in various food products. The company is known for its innovative and sustainable ingredient solutions that cater to the evolving needs of the industry.

name: Fortune Brands Innovations

The company's subsidiaries include leading brands in categories such as home security, plumbing, and outdoor living products. Fortune Brands Innovations, Inc. focuses on creating products that enhance the beauty, comfort, and security of consumers' homes.

name: PPL

It is engaged in the generation and marketing of electricity, primarily in the northeastern and western United States. PPL Corporation also manages regulated utilities in Kentucky and the United Kingdom, providing electricity and natural gas to customers. The company has a diverse energy portfolio that includes coal, natural gas, nuclear, hydro, and renewable energy sources. PPL Corporation is committed to sustainable practices and has made significant investments in renewable energy projects to reduce its carbon footprint.

name: Sanmina
description: Sanmina Corporation is an American electronics manufacturing services (EMS) provider headquartered in the United States. It provides end-to-end manufacturing solutions, including design, engineering, and fabrication of complex components and products. Sanmina serves various industries, such as communications networks, defense and aerospace, industrial, medical, multimedia, computing and storage, automotive, and clean technology. The company offers services such as product design and engineering, PCB fabrication, system assembly, logistics, repair, and after-market services. Founded in 1980, Sanmina has operations in over 25 countries and employs over 50,000 people worldwide.

name: Bed Bath & Beyond
description: Bed Bath & Beyond Inc. is a retail company that specializes in selling a wide range of domestic merchandise. Founded in 1971, the company offers products such as bedding, bathroom items, kitchenware, home decor, and various other household goods. Bed Bath & Beyond operates both online and through physical retail stores across the United States, Canada, and Mexico. The company is known for its large store format, extensive product selection, and its popular coupons and loyalty program.

name: Cintas
description: Cintas Corporation is an American company that provides a specialized business-to-business services, primarily in the areas of uniforms, facility services, and first aid and safety products. The company was founded in 1929 by Richard "Doc" Farmer in Cincinnati, Ohio. Cintas has grown to become a leading provider of corporate uniforms in North America, serving a wide range of industries such as healthcare, hospitality, and manufacturing. In addition to its uniform services, Cintas also offers document management, cleaning supplies, and other workplace essentials.

name: NCR
description: NCR Corporation, previously known as National Cash Register, is an American technology company that provides products and services that enable businesses to connect, interact, and transact with their customers. The company offers a wide range of solutions including point-of-sale terminals, self-service kiosks, automated teller machines (ATMs), barcode scanners, and software for industries such as retail, hospitality, financial services, and telecommunications. NCR Corporation has a long history dating back to its founding in 1884 and has since grown to become a leading provider of omni-channel technology solutions for businesses worldwide.

name: ABM Industries

It offers services such as electrical and lighting, energy solutions, facilities engineering, parking, and security, among others. ABM serves a diverse range of industries, including commercial, government, healthcare, industrial, and retail sectors. The company was founded in 1909 and has since grown to become a prominent player in the facility management industry.

name: Rockwell Automation
description: Rockwell Automation, Inc. is an American provider of industrial automation and information technology. The company designs, manufactures, and sells industrial automation products and services to a wide range of industries worldwide. With a focus on helping companies increase productivity, improve efficiency, and reduce costs, Rockwell Automation offers solutions such as control systems, sensors, software, and services for various industrial applications. The company was founded in 1903 and has since grown to become a leading player in the industrial automation sector.

name: Northern Trust
description: Northern Trust Corporation is a financial services company that specializes in wealth management, asset servicing, asset management, and banking. It was founded in 1889 and has since grown to become a leading provider of financial services globally. Northern Trust Corporation serves corporations, institutional investors, and high-net-worth individuals, offering a range of services such as investment management, trust and custody, banking, and fiduciary services. The company is known for its focus on professionalism, integrity, and client service, and it operates in multiple countries around the world.

name: XPO

XPO Logistics offers services such as freight brokerage, last-mile delivery, contract logistics, and supply chain management. It was founded in 2011 and has since grown to become a major player in the logistics industry, serving a wide range of industries including retail, e-commerce, healthcare, and aerospace.

name: Science Applications International
description: Science Applications International Corporation (SAIC) is an American company that specializes in government services and information technology. The company offers a wide range of services, including engineering, technology integration, and project management for various government agencies, particularly in the fields of defense, intelligence, and homeland security. SAIC was founded in 1969 and has since grown to become a prominent player in the government contracting industry. The company is known for its work on a variety of high-profile projects and has a strong reputation for delivering innovative solutions to its clients.

name: Ameren
description: Ameren Corporation is an American utility company that operates in the states of Missouri and Illinois. The company was formed in 1997 through the merger of Missouri-based Union Electric Company and Illinois-based CIPSCO Incorporated. Ameren serves over 2.4 million electric customers and more than 900,000 natural gas customers across its service territories. The company is involved in the generation, transmission, and distribution of electricity, as well as the distribution of natural gas. Ameren places a strong emphasis on sustainability and has set goals to reduce carbon emissions and increase the use of renewable energy sources in its power generation portfolio.

name: First American Financial
description: First American Financial Corporation is a financial services company that provides title insurance and settlement services to the real estate and mortgage industries. Founded in 1889, it offers services such as title insurance, property information, and other real estate-related services. The company operates through multiple segments including Title Insurance and Services, Specialty Insurance, and Corporate. First American Financial Corporation is one of the largest title insurance companies in the United States, with a wide range of services aimed at facilitating real estate transactions and protecting property ownership rights.

name: Bath & Body Works
description: Bath & Body Works, Inc. is an American retail company specializing in personal care and home fragrance products. It was founded in 1990 and is a subsidiary of L Brands. Bath & Body Works offers a wide range of products including body lotions, shower gels, perfumes, candles, and home fragrances. The company operates over 1,700 stores across the United States and has a strong online presence as well. Known for its signature scents and seasonal collections, Bath & Body Works is a popular destination for customers looking for high-quality bath and beauty products.

name: Regions Financial
description: Regions Financial Corporation is a bank holding company headquartered in the United States. It provides a range of banking and financial services such as retail and commercial banking, trust, securities brokerage, mortgage and insurance products. Regions operates through a network of branches and ATMs across multiple states in the South, Midwest, and Texas. The company serves individual customers, small businesses, and large corporations with various banking and financial solutions.

name: Activision Blizzard
description: Activision Blizzard, Inc. is an American video game holding company based in Santa Monica, California. The company was formed in 2008 by the merger of Activision, an international video game publisher, and Blizzard Entertainment, a developer of popular video games such as World of Warcraft and Overwatch. Activision Blizzard is known for publishing and developing a wide range of video games for various platforms, including console, PC, and mobile devices. The company is one of the largest and most successful in the video game industry, with a strong presence in esports and a dedicated fan base.

name: Avantor
description: Avantor, Inc. is an American company that specializes in providing products and services to customers in the biopharma, healthcare, education, and advanced technologies sectors. The company offers a wide range of products, including chemicals, lab supplies, and equipment used in research laboratories and production facilities. Avantor also provides custom manufacturing and other services to support the needs of its customers. The company was founded in 1904 and has since grown to become a leading supplier in the life sciences and advanced technology industries.

name: Genworth Financial
description: Genworth Financial, Inc. is an American Fortune 500 insurance company. The company provides insurance, wealth management, investment, and financial solutions. Genworth operates through three main segments: U.S. Life Insurance, International, and U.S. Mortgage Insurance. The company offers products such as life insurance, long-term care insurance, mortgage insurance, and annuities. The company is a leader in the Appalachian Basin, particularly in the Marcellus and Utica shales, and operates a large-scale, integrated energy business. EQT Corporation is committed to sustainable energy development and environmental stewardship while providing reliable energy to its customers.

Skechers designs, develops, and markets a wide range of athletic, casual, and fashionable footwear for men, women, and children. The company has grown to become one of the largest footwear brands in the United States, known for its diverse product offerings and trendy designs. Skechers operates in numerous countries worldwide and has a strong presence in the retail industry.

name: Landstar System

The company offers a range of transportation services, including truckload and less-than-truckload transportation, rail intermodal, air freight, ocean cargo, expedited ground and air delivery, warehousing, and customs brokerage. Landstar System, Inc. operates a decentralized business model, with independent agents and business capacity owners providing transportation capacity and logistics services to customers.

name: Knight-Swift Transportation Holdings
description: Knight-Swift Transportation Holdings Inc. is a transportation and trucking company formed by the merger of Knight Transportation and Swift Transportation in 2017. It is one of the largest trucking companies in the United States, providing a range of transportation and logistics services across North America. Knight-Swift operates a fleet of tractors, trailers, and refrigerated units to transport goods for a diverse customer base. The company is known for its commitment to safety, efficiency, and reliability in delivering freight services.

name: SVB Financial Group

The company operates through its primary subsidiary, Silicon Valley Bank, which offers commercial banking, investment banking, asset management, and private banking services. SVB Financial Group is known for its focus on serving the innovation economy and has a reputation for being a key financial partner for startup companies and growth-stage businesses in the technology and life sciences sectors.

name: Par Pacific Holdings

Originally established in 1984, the company has made significant investments in energy-related assets, including oil refineries, retail outlets, and logistics networks. Par Pacific Holdings, Inc. operates primarily in the western United States, with a focus on providing energy products and services to customers in the region. The company is committed to sustainability and operational excellence in its business practices.

name: Albemarle

The company was founded in 1994 and has since grown to become a major player in the specialty chemicals industry. Albemarle operates in three business segments: Lithium, Bromine Specialties, and Catalysts. The company's products are used in a wide range of applications, including energy storage, petroleum refining, pharmaceuticals, and more. Albemarle is known for its innovative and sustainable approaches to chemical manufacturing and is recognized as a leader in the development of lithium technologies for electric vehicles and energy storage systems.

name: Vulcan Materials
